1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,530
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:02,530 --> 00:00:04,280
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:07,760
Five people with sharp romance radars
have gathered.

4
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,710
Good to see you.
Things are blowing up right now.

5
00:00:10,710 --> 00:00:12,460
It's totally crazy.

6
00:00:12,460 --> 00:00:15,360
So crazy. My gosh.

7
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:18,290
Last week, they chose a date
who changed them the most.

8
00:00:18,290 --> 00:00:20,910
Seong Min and Min Ju went on a date but...

9
00:00:20,910 --> 00:00:22,560
They felt cold.

10
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:24,710
So was I.

11
00:00:24,710 --> 00:00:28,400
Why did Seong Min have to say
that he felt relieved?

12
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,610
I guess he really did.

13
00:00:30,610 --> 00:00:34,400
He could have had a clean end with Min Ju.

14
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,610
They could have become friends, but

15
00:00:36,610 --> 00:00:38,280
he wasn't trying to hurt her either.

16
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:40,660
He didn't mean to say it like that.

17
00:00:40,660 --> 00:00:45,400
As you said, I guess he was totally
clueless since he apologized.

18
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:50,920
He did apologize sincerely,
looking all flustered.

19
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:53,670
Right. He must have asked AI.

20
00:00:53,670 --> 00:00:58,740
I think he asked, "What did I do wrong?
How do I apologize?"

21
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:02,430
And Jun Hyeon and Yu Gyeong.

22
00:01:02,430 --> 00:01:05,640
Wow. Saying someone changed them

23
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:08,800
is a bit different than just liking someone.

24
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,120
And there was that famous line.

25
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:16,270
It's not romance without extravagance.

26
00:01:16,270 --> 00:01:19,810
We shortened it to "N.R.W.E."
to make it easier to memorize.

27
00:01:19,810 --> 00:01:24,650
He defined romance in his own style.

28
00:01:24,650 --> 00:01:29,620
Wu Yeol's expression during
the men's chat was telling.

29
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:32,320
Everyone was like, "Mine is Yu Gyeong."
"I am, too."

30
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:34,930
He got anxious whenever she was brought up.

31
00:01:34,930 --> 00:01:37,660
His attitude definitely changed a lot, right?

32
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:40,030
He doesn't know what to do.
He doesn't know what to do.

33
00:01:40,030 --> 00:01:42,350
Things went exactly like a TV drama.

34
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:45,400
A male lead suddenly realizes, like,

35
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:49,310
"I've been loving only you all this time."
And he regrets it.

36
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,720
That's how romance dramas go.

37
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,330
It feels like things are going that way.

38
00:01:53,330 --> 00:01:55,450
But so many people are into her already.

39
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:59,080
And the supporting male character
is getting more prominent.

40
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:03,030
- That's exactly how romance dramas go.
- That's right.

41
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,940
Here they are.

42
00:02:04,940 --> 00:02:07,200
[Min Ju and Seong Min
are home after their date]

43
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,090
They aren't saying anything.

44
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:14,540
[Min Ju is going upstairs quickly]

45
00:02:26,770 --> 00:02:28,200
[Sigh]

46
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:39,540
[Still feeling upset]

47
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,790
[Worried]

48
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,490
- Unni.
- Hey.

49
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:56,130
- I worked late today.
- Really?

50
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:07,690
I'm so tired because of that.

51
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:11,000
[Lying to hide that she's upset]

52
00:03:20,070 --> 00:03:23,250
- I'll let you rest.
- Okay.

53
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:33,530
[Seong Min is also feeling upset]

54
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:42,360
You don't look so good.

55
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,150
Did something happen?

56
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:51,110
- I think it's bad.
- You feel bad?

57
00:03:51,780 --> 00:03:54,180
I do, and I...

58
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:59,570
I'm not sure.

59
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,370
Why are you so upset?

60
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:12,910
It's about liking someone as a person
versus as a romantic partner.

61
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:14,650
I remember you mentioning it.

62
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:18,830
I thought I should tell Min Ju.

63
00:04:18,830 --> 00:04:21,530
[Wu Yeol and So Yun are home, too]

64
00:04:21,530 --> 00:04:23,670
- Yu Gyeong.
- What is it?

65
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:26,950
- You became a lady.
- Come on.

66
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:30,050
Are we feeling down?

67
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:33,120
He looked upset, so we were talking.

68
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,660
What is it, Hyung?

69
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,760
It's nothing.

70
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:43,420
At the Han River, I said I felt at ease.

71
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:48,190
She says she felt empty hearing that.

72
00:04:49,940 --> 00:04:51,170
[Nodding]

73
00:05:01,710 --> 00:05:05,430
She thought I meant, "I couldn't wait
to get this off my chest.

74
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:08,060
There's Min Ju. I'd better tell her today.

75
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:10,460
What a relief." Something like that.

76
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:15,400
I wanted to check if I liked her
as a person or a romantic partner.

77
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:20,240
Of course, I'm attracted to her,
but more as a person.

78
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:23,020
I find her very easy to talk to.

79
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:25,250
So...

80
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:31,150
I thought I was more attracted
to her as a person.

81
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:34,150
Because of the timing you told her that,

82
00:05:34,150 --> 00:05:36,530
I can totally understand how she feels.

83
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:39,770
She poured herself into you,
and you had a connection.

84
00:05:39,770 --> 00:05:44,540
She could feel that way because
of what you've displayed.

85
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:46,320
And it can't be completely platonic, either.

86
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:49,790
Everyone here has romantic
feelings for each other.

87
00:05:49,790 --> 00:05:51,500
We didn't come here to make friends.

88
00:05:51,500 --> 00:05:53,150
Right, right.

89
00:05:53,150 --> 00:05:56,210
I felt like everything I had to say
would sound like an excuse.

90
00:05:56,210 --> 00:05:59,780
It'll be like I'm denying it.

91
00:05:59,780 --> 00:06:02,260
So, I asked AI earlier.

92
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:04,660
I was like, "I don't know what to do."

93
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:09,470
But Seong Min, I never expected
anything ever since I came here.

94
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:12,400
I've never done something

95
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:17,240
expecting anything in return. Not even once.

96
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:20,680
I wish I could be like you.

97
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:24,050
You think what you say
will sound like an excuse.

98
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:27,660
I'm trying to tell you that you
shouldn't think that way.

99
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:30,140
There's no need to think that way.

100
00:06:36,010 --> 00:06:39,020
[Thinking]

101
00:06:39,020 --> 00:06:41,010
Yu Gyeong...

102
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,100
and Jun Hyeon?

103
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:04,340
You talked about liking someone
as a person versus as a romantic partner.

104
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,840
How did we come to this?

105
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:09,820
It's about what you feel more.

106
00:07:10,730 --> 00:07:14,070
When I'm with Jun Hyeon,

107
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:17,590
I seem to laugh more.

108
00:07:17,590 --> 00:07:18,700
Right, it seems that way.

109
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:21,710
And I feel very comfortable.

110
00:07:21,710 --> 00:07:25,580
I used to feel least comfortable with him.

111
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:29,070
But at some point,
he became the most comfortable.

112
00:07:29,070 --> 00:07:33,700
Wu Yeol's lips are drying as
he hears Jun Hyun's strength.

113
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:39,300
I think my feelings for Jun Hyeon
are the most complex.

114
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,830
- Gosh, I feel threatened.
- He is threatened.

115
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:46,260
Should we go back home?
Should we take this to go?

116
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:47,510
I can't wait.

117
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:49,730
The women like Jun Hyeon.

118
00:07:49,730 --> 00:07:52,710
He just heard that coming from another woman.

119
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:07,870
[Noticed]

120
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:09,480
What are you up to?

121
00:08:14,050 --> 00:08:17,400
- Leather looks good on you.
- Really?

122
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:21,130
But I ended up wearing it today.

123
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:24,210
I know. You'll never be able
to wear it again.

124
00:08:24,210 --> 00:08:26,950
I wore a dress today, too.

125
00:08:26,950 --> 00:08:29,460
I didn't expect to see So Yun.

126
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:31,120
Really?

127
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:38,410
It made me wish
that we had talked a lot more.

128
00:08:38,410 --> 00:08:39,870
Really?

129
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:45,870
What's the last thing you'd like to do?

130
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:50,440
- What do I want to do?
- If you get to spend all day.

131
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:56,540
It's more about who I'm with.

132
00:08:57,310 --> 00:09:00,180
- What about me?
- With you?

133
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:04,030
- A drive-in theater?
- That would be amazing.

134
00:09:04,030 --> 00:09:06,580
I don't know if we'd get a chance.

135
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:08,420
It's such a shame.

136
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:13,310
There's nothing we can do.

137
00:09:13,310 --> 00:09:15,120
It's a shame.

138
00:09:17,330 --> 00:09:18,950
Such a shame.

139
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:22,940
- Should we take the trash out?
- Yes.

140
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:26,250
- We need to take it out.
- We set a new record.

141
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:29,700
- Is this for real?
- What do you want to do?

142
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:32,270
- I want to separate them.
- You do?

143
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,880
We can do that.

144
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:37,760
Can you recycle this?

145
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:40,730
- I think this is trash.
- That's trash.

146
00:09:42,230 --> 00:09:43,450
What?

147
00:09:44,180 --> 00:09:47,720
Oppa, why are you so sensitive?

148
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:51,190
No, I'm not. I'm in a great mood right now.

149
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:53,310
I'm more sensitive.

150
00:09:53,310 --> 00:09:55,080
Don't be.

151
00:09:56,220 --> 00:09:58,420
Don't be sensitive, I said.

152
00:10:03,830 --> 00:10:07,430
- I was a bit sensitive today.
- Today? Why?

153
00:10:07,430 --> 00:10:08,800
Because it wasn't you.

154
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,190
I wanted to have dinner with you.

155
00:10:10,190 --> 00:10:15,970
Oh, there's a reason for that.

156
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:22,650
Should we just take these for now?

157
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,700
[They had sorted out trash once before]

158
00:10:30,710 --> 00:10:33,430
Let's take this out. I'll eat it.

159
00:10:33,430 --> 00:10:36,260
- This makes him so likable.
- I know.

160
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,660
- Did you have dinner?
- No, I'm hungry.

161
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:42,280
- Did you have lunch?
- I had Greek yogurt.

162
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:44,940
Greek yogurt? Good job.

163
00:10:44,940 --> 00:10:47,620
- Cute shoes.
- I know, right?

164
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:52,940
- That outfit looks familiar.
- What? Do you recognize it?

165
00:10:52,940 --> 00:10:54,550
- I wore it on the first day.
- Really?

166
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:56,580
I wore this when we cooked together.

167
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:58,770
I knew it.

168
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:00,970
[They tried to save the ruined pasta dish]

169
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:04,240
- I'll get dressed. Let's go together.
- Okay. I'll wait.

170
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:08,150
[They went out to get sauce
on their first chaotic night]

171
00:11:08,150 --> 00:11:10,350
Gosh, seriously.

172
00:11:10,350 --> 00:11:13,300
You don't have to feel so stressed.

173
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:17,190
[They went out together again tonight]

174
00:11:17,190 --> 00:11:19,460
This is how it is.

175
00:11:21,210 --> 00:11:27,300
[Feeling as if the memories
of the past seemed inevitable]

176
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:30,920
[Early morning]

177
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:33,640
- So pretty.
- Min Ju.

178
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:43,540
I wanted to make you something tasty.

179
00:11:46,060 --> 00:11:48,760
You have to try my French toast.

180
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,720
Right. I haven't tried it.

181
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,630
I haven't tried it yet.

182
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:59,660
- Her head is somewhere else right now.
- I'm sure she's upset.

183
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:03,870
[Meanwhile at the house]

184
00:12:08,560 --> 00:12:11,070
What's the last thing you'd like to do?

185
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:16,340
It's more about who I'm with.

186
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:18,500
So much to think about.

187
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:21,620
[There is a lot to think about this morning]

188
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:34,480
There's our Seo Won.

189
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:42,120
- Yu Gyeong.
- Yes?

190
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:45,370
Want to have coffee on the rooftop together?

191
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:47,170
Does this sound good? Yes.

192
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:48,490
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

193
00:12:48,490 --> 00:12:50,000
They're just friends.

194
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,910
[Making drip coffee]

195
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:55,620
I'm all ready to go.

196
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:58,370
Are you ready to be up there for hours?

197
00:12:58,370 --> 00:13:00,130
It's cold.

198
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:02,410
- Did you get some sleep?
- Yes.

199
00:13:02,410 --> 00:13:06,850
- I had a serious chat with So Yun.
- Serious chat?

200
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:09,710
You need to have one with me today, too.

201
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,520
Yes, let's.

202
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:14,750
- I'm serious.
- I'm totally serious.

203
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:16,310
I'm really serious.

204
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:18,840
You don't know how serious I am, huh?

205
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:21,590
Are you ready to cry?

206
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:28,130
- Do it slowly.
- I guess they're in the same situation.

207
00:13:29,020 --> 00:13:30,800
[Water keeps spilling]

208
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,890
I love it. I love it.

209
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:35,870
Why is it spilling so much?

210
00:13:35,870 --> 00:13:38,250
I got it. I got it.

211
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:41,130
I love it. It works so well.

212
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:44,690
I'm hearing a lot of birds.

213
00:13:44,690 --> 00:13:47,140
- Birds?
- Yes. This place is great.

214
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:48,350
It is.

215
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:50,160
We never went on a date once.

216
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:53,060
- Right, they never did.
- Why do you think that is?

217
00:13:53,060 --> 00:13:55,310
Maybe neither of us wanted it.

218
00:13:55,310 --> 00:13:57,280
To be honest, that's true.

219
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:00,170
- You went out with everyone but me.
- That's right.

220
00:14:00,170 --> 00:14:02,520
Will we ever go out?

221
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:04,310
You hate me, don't you?

222
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:08,150
You aren't interested in me.

223
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:09,950
What are you doing tomorrow, Yu Gyeong?

224
00:14:09,950 --> 00:14:11,780
What?

225
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:15,590
- What?
- Want to have a date with me?

226
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:19,350
No, I don't want to get to know you.

227
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:22,120
- Don't try to force me.
- Let's get to know each other, Oppa.

228
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:25,130
That's enough, seriously.

229
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:27,260
There are relationships like that.

230
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:35,180
I need to apologize to you about something.

231
00:14:36,590 --> 00:14:39,640
Before I came here,

232
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:43,010
I thought being the same age
makes you feel comfortable.

233
00:14:43,010 --> 00:14:46,930
- I said I was most shocked by you.
- Really?

234
00:14:46,930 --> 00:14:48,270
After hearing your age.

235
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:51,520
- Right, right. Her first impression.
- So, I think...

236
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:55,390
I had a bit of prejudice
against you at first.

237
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:57,010
I didn't know. I had no idea.

238
00:14:57,010 --> 00:14:58,940
He shut her down
after hearing she was younger.

239
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,077
I'm sorry.

240
00:15:00,077 --> 00:15:03,150
That's why you create distance with me.

241
00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:05,940
No, I didn't. I didn't go that far.

242
00:15:05,940 --> 00:15:10,170
I felt it. Just kidding. Not at all.

243
00:15:11,355 --> 00:15:13,510
We've both been busy.

244
00:15:13,510 --> 00:15:14,991
True. They were both busy.

245
00:15:14,991 --> 00:15:17,665
I was busy from the get-go,
caring for myself.

246
00:15:17,665 --> 00:15:20,765
You're so busy. You're a busy girl.

247
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:23,280
Right.

248
00:15:24,490 --> 00:15:27,100
- I think I'll see the person tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?

249
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,960
Tomorrow.

250
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:34,840
I saw him yesterday and will
probably see him tomorrow.

251
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,400
The same person?

252
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:40,170
- No?
- Someone else?

253
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:42,230
I'm still torn.

254
00:15:42,230 --> 00:15:45,160
Between Wu Yeol and Jun Hyeon?

255
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:48,890
As I get to know each person,

256
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:52,900
I find them more charming.

257
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:56,180
- Doesn't it drive you crazy?
- Yes, I'm going crazy.

258
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:59,100
Everyone has their own unique charm.

259
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:02,480
You feel conflicted
every time you go on a date.

260
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,870
Right.

261
00:16:04,870 --> 00:16:08,600
I'm guessing you felt that way a lot.

262
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:10,960
- Right?
- Right.

263
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:16,120
Do you feel anxious?

264
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:17,660
Anxious?

265
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:20,830
I always do, especially here.

266
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:26,000
I should try to temper it as much as I can.

267
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:29,110
What about you?

268
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:33,370
I feel so anxious.

269
00:16:33,370 --> 00:16:37,010
I've been dreaming a lot.
A lot of bad dreams.

270
00:16:37,010 --> 00:16:40,650
I've been dreaming about people here
for seven days in a row.

271
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:42,730
- I have, too.
- About having conversations like this.

272
00:16:42,730 --> 00:16:46,460
For me, it's different situations.

273
00:16:46,460 --> 00:16:48,320
I wake up, and I'm like...

274
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:52,070
- You dream about what you imagined?
- Yes.

275
00:16:52,070 --> 00:16:56,580
I'm realizing how stressed I am these days.

276
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:00,280
You're on a roller coaster.

277
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:07,760
Can I keep riding the roller coaster?

278
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:10,170
- You feel anxious?
- Yes.

279
00:17:11,950 --> 00:17:14,000
[Anxiety is hard to control]

280
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:19,770
One of them says
he only wants to get to know me.

281
00:17:19,770 --> 00:17:23,220
He doesn't demand or expect anything.

282
00:17:23,220 --> 00:17:25,270
He tries not to pressure me.

283
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:28,350
- I've always noticed that.
- It paid off.

284
00:17:28,350 --> 00:17:30,340
- That's so cool.
- Yes.

285
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:35,250
One person is like a swan boat.

286
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:37,980
A swan boat versus a roller coaster.

287
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:40,630
- They have different charms.
- Right.

288
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:47,090
[They're totally opposite]

289
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:49,680
[Her worries are growing]

290
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:55,460
We imagined dating one person after this.

291
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:57,970
If you think about it,

292
00:18:00,390 --> 00:18:03,740
it always brings heartache.
No matter how much you love them.

293
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:05,270
So...

294
00:18:08,210 --> 00:18:10,140
In the end,

295
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:13,570
just find the person you like more.

296
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:18,540
Find a person you like more. You can.

297
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:21,000
- This is amazing.
- Someone you like more.

298
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,970
I've been wanting to tell you that.

299
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:27,720
He's right. It's a roller coaster
because they all live together.

300
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,790
You're so mature.

301
00:18:29,790 --> 00:18:32,570
I'll call you "oppa" from now on.

302
00:18:32,570 --> 00:18:35,360
Little sis, shall we drink?

303
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:37,070
Oppa.

304
00:18:41,790 --> 00:18:43,620
What do I do now?

305
00:18:44,430 --> 00:18:46,090
You can do it.

306
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:50,010
Get up. Let's say "fighting"
three times and go in.

307
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:52,490
Say it loud on the count of three.

308
00:18:52,490 --> 00:18:55,210
- You have to do it, okay?
- Of course, I will.

309
00:18:55,210 --> 00:18:57,890
I'll say it loudly to cheer for both of us.

310
00:18:57,890 --> 00:19:01,090
- I'll say it loudly to cheer for myself.
- Let's do it like this.

311
00:19:01,090 --> 00:19:02,660
Say "fighting" on a count of three.

312
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:06,240
- One, two, three. Fighting!
- Fighting!

313
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:10,630
How nice.

314
00:19:10,630 --> 00:19:12,980
- I can do it.
- I feel energized.

315
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:15,290
- Do you?
- Of course.

316
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:18,020
That was like a scene in a movie.

317
00:19:18,020 --> 00:19:20,850
The main topic was roller coaster.

318
00:19:20,850 --> 00:19:24,000
Will I keep riding a roller coaster
after this?

319
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,680
The swan boat is like the second option.

320
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:28,990
You can ride a swan boat for life.

321
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:31,860
- Who rides a swan boat for life?
- You can't ride a roller coaster all day.

322
00:19:31,860 --> 00:19:34,630
I think Wu Yeol was
at the center of her thoughts.

323
00:19:34,630 --> 00:19:38,860
He told her to choose the one
she likes the most and to date.

324
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:42,820
He is exactly right.

325
00:19:42,820 --> 00:19:44,810
I'm impressed with him.

326
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:46,420
Cheer up.

327
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:52,610
[Seo Won is getting ready to go out]

328
00:19:52,610 --> 00:19:53,990
[Grabbing]

329
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,780
[Putting in his mouth]

330
00:20:02,870 --> 00:20:04,530
[Chewing]

331
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:13,400
Yu Gyeong, use this before a date.
It's so refreshing.

332
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:18,090
- You put it on your tongue.
- Okay, thank you.

333
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:25,550
[Min Ju is returning to Signal House]

334
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:27,450
What should we have for dinner?

335
00:20:27,450 --> 00:20:29,650
I know. Dinner...

336
00:20:29,650 --> 00:20:32,240
[Going out to get groceries]

337
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:35,020
The weather is so nice.

338
00:20:35,020 --> 00:20:37,550
It's really nice.

339
00:20:37,550 --> 00:20:40,240
- I love this kind of weather.
- Really?

340
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,570
Gosh, should we run?

341
00:20:42,570 --> 00:20:45,080
[The weather makes them want to run]

342
00:20:48,210 --> 00:20:52,480
There is no guarantee that
Wu Yeol will come home.

343
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:56,050
- Always about Wu Yeol.
- I'm hurting the most.

344
00:20:56,050 --> 00:20:58,590
- You don't know about me, huh?
- I don't.

345
00:20:58,590 --> 00:20:59,940
It's true.

346
00:20:59,940 --> 00:21:03,630
Once I talked to him tonight,

347
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:06,910
- I'll feel more sorted out.
- Really?

348
00:21:06,910 --> 00:21:10,730
There are a few things I need to figure out.

349
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:17,190
[Starting to make dinner]

350
00:21:18,970 --> 00:21:20,740
Come here, you guys.

351
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:23,330
It's more food than I thought.

352
00:21:23,330 --> 00:21:26,270
I thought everyone would be home.

353
00:21:26,270 --> 00:21:29,210
A dinner between two lonely women.

354
00:21:29,210 --> 00:21:33,130
- Two ladies who are going through a lot.
- I'm going crazy.

355
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:36,720
[The two lonely women's selfie]

356
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:39,460
Huh? What? Who's this?

357
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:40,860
She is so clearly excited.

358
00:21:40,860 --> 00:21:43,840
It's obviously Seong Min because it's 8:00.

359
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,310
[Glancing]

360
00:21:45,310 --> 00:21:46,610
Gosh.

361
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,400
- What are you doing?
- Hi.

362
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,130
Hi, hi. What are you up to?

363
00:21:51,130 --> 00:21:53,090
- It happens to be those two.
- Smells good.

364
00:21:53,090 --> 00:21:55,630
We cooked.

365
00:21:55,630 --> 00:21:59,990
- How can you eat now?
- I'll put this in the room.

366
00:21:59,990 --> 00:22:02,490
Where should I set his utensils?

367
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:05,080
- I'll eat quickly and go upstairs.
- Why?

368
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,910
Just because.

369
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:10,510
Do you not want him to sit here?

370
00:22:10,510 --> 00:22:12,260
I might as well sit next to him.

371
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:15,620
Side by side is better
when you don't want to talk.

372
00:22:15,620 --> 00:22:18,050
Just make sure you don't get indigestion.

373
00:22:19,580 --> 00:22:21,470
The shrimp is not cooked.

374
00:22:21,470 --> 00:22:23,280
What?

375
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:25,240
I'll just remove the shrimp.

376
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,960
[Seong Min is coming downstairs]

377
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:32,670
You cook so much. You cook so much.

378
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,680
We cooked for about four people.

379
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,920
She's just staring at the microwave.

380
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:40,570
[Staring]

381
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:44,350
[Glancing]

382
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:52,570
- Are you making something else?
- No, I'm microwaving.

383
00:22:52,570 --> 00:22:54,320
So awkward.

384
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,530
What are you carrying? Isn't it hot?

385
00:22:57,530 --> 00:23:00,780
- What's that? Why did you make so much?
- It's shrimp.

386
00:23:03,150 --> 00:23:05,650
How can you eat like that?

387
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,460
Did you come home a while ago?

388
00:23:09,460 --> 00:23:11,170
[Nodding]

389
00:23:12,630 --> 00:23:15,060
[Min Ju is eating quietly]

390
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:20,790
She's staring at the sesame seeds.

391
00:23:26,710 --> 00:23:28,430
[Min Ju leaves first]

392
00:23:28,430 --> 00:23:30,550
So uncomfortable.

393
00:23:32,170 --> 00:23:33,400
[Turning]

394
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:40,900
[Pausing]

395
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:43,990
You can go upstairs. You can go upstairs.

396
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:48,230
Yu Gyeong is so quick. "You can go upstairs."

397
00:23:48,230 --> 00:23:50,370
I'll do the dishes.

398
00:23:50,370 --> 00:23:51,960
Just leave them.

399
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:54,370
[Knock, knock]

400
00:23:55,270 --> 00:23:56,420
Yes?

401
00:23:56,420 --> 00:23:57,970
Min Ju?

402
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:07,630
- Are you eating something?
- I'm having a snack.

403
00:24:07,630 --> 00:24:10,630
- Should we go in there?
- Look at her expression. Wow!

404
00:24:10,630 --> 00:24:12,900
Min Ju's expression.

405
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,800
Bring the snack with you.

406
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,730
Should we talk in 20 minutes?

407
00:24:22,730 --> 00:24:26,020
Okay, in 20 minutes.

408
00:24:26,020 --> 00:24:27,760
I'll be back in 20 minutes.

409
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:31,390
[Yu Gyeong is waiting for someone]

410
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:35,230
Someone's here. Someone's here.
Is it Wu Yeol?

411
00:24:36,653 --> 00:24:39,303
It's Wu Yeol.

412
00:24:54,430 --> 00:24:56,520
What tasty food are you eating?

413
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:58,740
I ate it all.

414
00:25:01,430 --> 00:25:03,890
What's this? Plum juice?

415
00:25:03,890 --> 00:25:06,870
- Did you have dinner?
- I had dinner.

416
00:25:07,870 --> 00:25:10,110
Hi, were you eating?

417
00:25:10,110 --> 00:25:12,280
I didn't eat much
because I already had dinner.

418
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:15,100
- Oh, yeah? Is someone else home?
- Min Ju.

419
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:18,280
Okay, I'll get changed real quick.

420
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:27,390
[Last night]

421
00:25:31,490 --> 00:25:36,830
I think I said something
unnecessary to you yesterday.

422
00:25:36,830 --> 00:25:38,950
Me? When?

423
00:25:38,950 --> 00:25:41,300
Regarding Seong Min.

424
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:44,370
You don't look so well.

425
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:50,010
No, I was just a bit bothered by something.

426
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:58,250
Oh, really?

427
00:25:58,250 --> 00:26:00,740
It's unavoidable.

428
00:26:00,740 --> 00:26:02,660
I'm okay.

429
00:26:03,430 --> 00:26:05,630
I'm a C.B.

430
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:10,620
- What's C.B?
- A clueless bastard.

431
00:26:11,710 --> 00:26:13,860
No.

432
00:26:13,860 --> 00:26:16,570
[Yu Gyeong is feeling uncomfortable]

433
00:26:20,910 --> 00:26:23,940
- Are you in a bad mood?
- My mood?

434
00:26:23,940 --> 00:26:25,370
It's nothing.

435
00:26:25,370 --> 00:26:28,800
I prefer it when they just ask,
"Are you in a bad mood?"

436
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:32,760
- I guess I have a lot to think about.
- Right.

437
00:26:36,020 --> 00:26:37,590
Is that so?

438
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:42,560
Should we go on a date
on Saturday if you're free?

439
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:44,600
- Saturday? Tomorrow?
- Yes.

440
00:26:45,450 --> 00:26:48,300
That would be nice.

441
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:50,620
Sounds good.

442
00:26:50,620 --> 00:26:52,560
Does it? Should we go to a drive-in theater?

443
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:54,300
- Really?
- Yes.

444
00:26:54,990 --> 00:26:56,500
Sounds good.

445
00:26:57,620 --> 00:27:00,240
And? What else do you want to do?

446
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,920
What about you?

447
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:06,280
- What do I want to do?
- Yes.

448
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:08,730
I'll come up with something.

449
00:27:08,730 --> 00:27:11,000
Please do. Come up with three.

450
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,090
Three? I will.

451
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:15,760
He's so caring.

452
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:20,600
Didn't you say you were tired today?

453
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:24,440
- What do you mean?
- You said you were tired.

454
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,760
- Earlier?
- Yeah.

455
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:27,790
I'm so tired today.

456
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:30,310
- I almost died on the way back.
- Did you doze off?

457
00:27:30,310 --> 00:27:33,080
It was such a short drive.

458
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:35,060
I was terrified.

459
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:43,700
I noticed you seemed down when I came home.

460
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:47,190
I have a lot on my mind. Just kidding.

461
00:27:47,190 --> 00:27:50,660
- I prepared for our office's move.
- Really?

462
00:27:51,890 --> 00:27:53,560
That's why I'm late.

463
00:27:54,530 --> 00:27:59,020
We're always laughing
and goofing around outside.

464
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:01,620
But we're so serious when we're here.

465
00:28:01,620 --> 00:28:03,440
What's the reason?

466
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:11,330
I want to joke around and laugh
when I see you.

467
00:28:11,330 --> 00:28:13,950
Who is it? Who did this to you?

468
00:28:23,220 --> 00:28:25,270
I don't want you to tiptoe around me.

469
00:28:25,270 --> 00:28:28,830
But it seems like you have.

470
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:30,860
I forgot all about it
while talking to you just now.

471
00:28:30,860 --> 00:28:34,140
I am no longer tiptoeing.

472
00:28:35,010 --> 00:28:37,640
It's because we are that type.

473
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:40,310
The type who moves on quickly.

474
00:28:40,310 --> 00:28:42,190
No one can top us.

475
00:28:44,190 --> 00:28:47,630
- Your eyes look a little further apart.
- Really?

476
00:28:47,630 --> 00:28:49,460
Should I hit my head? Put them back together.

477
00:28:49,460 --> 00:28:51,290
I love conversations like this.

478
00:28:52,050 --> 00:28:53,250
[Opening eyes wide]

479
00:28:57,180 --> 00:28:59,250
Look at her laughing.

480
00:28:59,250 --> 00:29:00,960
Why are you suddenly shifting gears?

481
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,820
What do you mean?

482
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:05,960
My stomach hurts.

483
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:12,210
If we hang out tomorrow,

484
00:29:12,210 --> 00:29:14,460
let's have fun.

485
00:29:15,750 --> 00:29:18,020
I always have fun with you.

486
00:29:18,020 --> 00:29:19,710
It's always been fun.

487
00:29:19,710 --> 00:29:23,440
Forget about all worries and stress.

488
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:27,100
- Check out the weather tomorrow.
- 17 degrees?

489
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:30,960
- It's spring weather.
- What should I wear?

490
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:33,330
- Is it the ideal temperature?
- Yes.

491
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:37,120
- It's perfect.
- If somebody asks you out, say no.

492
00:29:37,740 --> 00:29:39,970
Even if you do?

493
00:29:39,970 --> 00:29:41,650
Why me?

494
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:46,590
It's a shame you wore leather yesterday.

495
00:29:46,590 --> 00:29:48,120
I'll wear it again tomorrow.

496
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:51,370
Pick an outfit for me in the closet.

497
00:29:51,370 --> 00:29:53,060
I'll wear it.

498
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:56,160
- What do you say?
- Sounds good.

499
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:59,640
I'll dress in the style you want.

500
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:10,130
We'll be able to hang out tomorrow, right?

501
00:30:13,550 --> 00:30:15,320
We have to.

502
00:30:18,590 --> 00:30:20,770
I'll sleep less if I have to.

503
00:30:20,770 --> 00:30:23,900
- He keeps making her heart flutter.
- I know.

504
00:30:25,180 --> 00:30:27,460
[There is only one question for today]

505
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:33,700
[What are you afraid of
before you start a relationship?]

506
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:35,900
The future...

507
00:30:39,610 --> 00:30:43,260
What am I afraid of
before I start a relationship?

508
00:30:44,820 --> 00:30:49,840
I wondered if he would know
if the letter was from me.

509
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:51,690
I was worried.

510
00:30:52,510 --> 00:30:54,890
You have a big heart.

511
00:30:54,890 --> 00:30:58,380
Was he able to see me accurately?

512
00:30:58,380 --> 00:31:01,010
Will he understand me well?

513
00:31:01,010 --> 00:31:04,720
I'm the least serious when I'm with you.

514
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:07,420
I actually like serious talks.

515
00:31:07,420 --> 00:31:11,290
I always have serious
conversations with my friends.

516
00:31:11,290 --> 00:31:17,070
But when I'm with you,
I always want to make you laugh.

517
00:31:17,070 --> 00:31:21,660
I guess I like it when you laugh.

518
00:31:21,660 --> 00:31:25,540
How do you start
a serious conversation, Unni?

519
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:30,200
I think I only have serious
conversations with some people.

520
00:31:30,200 --> 00:31:36,560
Right? But I can have serious
conversations with everyone.

521
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:37,650
Really?

522
00:31:37,650 --> 00:31:41,900
- But I can't with Wu Yeol.
- Really?

523
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:46,480
I'm wondering if I should
initiate it, but how do I?

524
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:49,130
I think it will be funny
when you guys get serious.

525
00:31:49,130 --> 00:31:51,070
I know.

526
00:31:51,070 --> 00:31:53,550
What kind of life have you been living?

527
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:54,440
[Embarrassed]

528
00:31:55,670 --> 00:31:57,820
- I think it'll be funny.
- I know.

529
00:31:57,820 --> 00:31:59,720
"As for me..."

530
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:04,320
You know that he moved to Seoul
alone after leaving the army.

531
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:07,520
- He hardly talked about that with me.
- Really?

532
00:32:08,900 --> 00:32:10,940
You can start now.

533
00:32:20,430 --> 00:32:22,670
Why are your eyes so...

534
00:32:27,490 --> 00:32:30,370
They have a story to tell.

535
00:32:30,370 --> 00:32:32,430
I've been through a lot.

536
00:32:34,470 --> 00:32:38,910
Let's have a productive day
because it's our last date.

537
00:32:38,910 --> 00:32:41,690
- Do you want to ride a swan boat?
- A swan boat?

538
00:32:41,690 --> 00:32:43,930
- Okay, okay.
- But you're a roller coaster.

539
00:32:43,930 --> 00:32:47,190
The first round is a trial. Give me a pass.

540
00:32:49,770 --> 00:32:51,380
What else is there?

541
00:32:53,070 --> 00:32:54,960
Should we go painting?

542
00:32:55,730 --> 00:32:58,120
I can't paint. Forget about that.

543
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,980
I want to go to your go-to spot.

544
00:32:59,980 --> 00:33:01,470
The malatang spot in front of my house.

545
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:02,750
Should we get malatang?

546
00:33:02,750 --> 00:33:05,760
- Come on, I don't want to.
- Why not?

547
00:33:07,070 --> 00:33:09,730
Why are you making me choose again?

548
00:33:09,730 --> 00:33:11,610
I'm thinking right now.

549
00:33:11,610 --> 00:33:14,700
I'm thinking right now. Really.

550
00:33:15,870 --> 00:33:19,770
- I'm suddenly coming up with ideas.
- Are you inspired? Keep going.

551
00:33:19,770 --> 00:33:21,000
Should we see a musical?

552
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,350
Should we go to Namsan Tower?

553
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:23,680
Should we hang a lock together?

554
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:26,550
Wow. That's not bad, Oppa.

555
00:33:26,550 --> 00:33:28,510
Does that sound good?
I've never done it before.

556
00:33:28,510 --> 00:33:31,170
- I've never been to Namsan Tower.
- Me neither.

557
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:34,660
Bring the straw sandal tomorrow.

558
00:33:36,990 --> 00:33:39,120
Should we go buy a camera?

559
00:33:39,850 --> 00:33:42,200
Let's write a list.

560
00:33:43,140 --> 00:33:46,630
- Take photos after buying a camera.
- Buy and photo shoot.

561
00:33:46,630 --> 00:33:49,720
[A thorough date plan]

562
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:55,550
We're going to need two days to do all this.

563
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:05,970
Let's go after all this.

564
00:34:05,970 --> 00:34:07,080
[Pausing]

565
00:34:07,850 --> 00:34:09,720
- Was that too smooth?
- Daebak.

566
00:34:09,720 --> 00:34:11,640
I almost answered.

567
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:13,260
"Who said I would?"

568
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:16,410
"Why would I?"

569
00:34:21,950 --> 00:34:23,270
[Smiling]

570
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:24,760
Why are they so cute?

571
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:26,770
Let's watch them all day.

572
00:34:28,070 --> 00:34:30,200
I didn't think we would end up here.

573
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:32,880
[Seong Min and Min Ju are in the tea room]

574
00:34:39,190 --> 00:34:42,040
How should I say this?

575
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:48,152
I thought about how I felt one more time.

576
00:34:48,152 --> 00:34:53,932
You've been so supportive of me
all this time.

577
00:34:57,570 --> 00:35:00,520
- What I said to you...
- Hold on.

578
00:35:00,520 --> 00:35:03,370
I'm sorry I said that in that situation.

579
00:35:07,970 --> 00:35:10,180
I was so thoughtless.

580
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:18,580
I think my direction was totally off.

581
00:35:23,290 --> 00:35:27,170
He still apologized to make her feel better.

582
00:35:27,170 --> 00:35:28,710
True.

583
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:34,810
But I think I was...

584
00:35:39,630 --> 00:35:42,530
I was inconsiderate, as you said. I'm sorry.

585
00:35:46,250 --> 00:35:48,800
Don't cry, please.

586
00:36:00,510 --> 00:36:02,830
You don't have to feel bad.

587
00:36:02,830 --> 00:36:04,900
You really don't have to.

588
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:11,280
You just have to be honest
about your feelings.

589
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:16,530
- I don't know why I keep worrying, either.
- Really?

590
00:36:16,530 --> 00:36:19,020
I'm not upset. I'm okay.

591
00:36:19,020 --> 00:36:22,740
I just don't want you to feel bad for me.

592
00:36:22,740 --> 00:36:29,360
Once you feel that way, it will be
hard to sustain our relationship.

593
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,660
[She didn't want his apology]

594
00:36:30,660 --> 00:36:34,130
She's been tormented all this time.

595
00:36:38,970 --> 00:36:41,260
Earlier, I asked Yu Gyeong

596
00:36:43,310 --> 00:36:47,640
if she has someone she won't
be able to see after this.

597
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:08,450
I'm thinking we might not be able to.

598
00:37:25,590 --> 00:37:27,530
You're done talking, right?

599
00:37:27,530 --> 00:37:29,260
[Nodding]

600
00:37:30,580 --> 00:37:33,540
I wish you luck until the end.

601
00:37:36,230 --> 00:37:38,170
[Leaving]

602
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:46,020
[Where did things go wrong?]

603
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:54,460
I'm glad she made up her mind.

604
00:37:54,460 --> 00:37:58,860
[For a long time]

605
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:03,520
[Seong Min wasn't able to leave the tea room]

606
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:19,140
[Min Ju also paced around feeling upset]

607
00:38:19,140 --> 00:38:23,630
She's learning to protect herself.

608
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:37,090
[Looking around]

609
00:38:49,170 --> 00:38:55,320
[Revisiting his thoughts]

610
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:58,440
Of course, I'm attracted to her,
but more as a person.

611
00:38:58,440 --> 00:39:01,340
I find her very easy to talk to.

612
00:39:01,340 --> 00:39:03,440
I can't say anything cheesy.

613
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:06,550
- It feels like it's just us two.
- Really?

614
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:11,980
I'm starting to feel comfortable. It's nice.

615
00:39:14,580 --> 00:39:17,190
[Can he resolve this misunderstanding?]

616
00:39:17,190 --> 00:39:19,280
What's he going to do?

617
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:32,480
[Knock, knock]

618
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:33,800
Yes.

619
00:39:36,550 --> 00:39:38,470
Min Ju...

620
00:39:38,470 --> 00:39:41,850
Just one second. Min Ju, it's Seong Min.

621
00:39:41,850 --> 00:39:43,720
He wants to see her again?

622
00:39:44,690 --> 00:39:48,860
[Attempting another conversation]

623
00:39:48,860 --> 00:39:51,100
Where is it? I wrote it down here.

624
00:39:51,100 --> 00:39:54,830
I don't have to see it, but I wrote it down.

625
00:39:57,570 --> 00:40:02,320
I thought about things
before I talked to you.

626
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:04,940
But it didn't go so smoothly.

627
00:40:05,690 --> 00:40:09,960
It looks like I drew a line.

628
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:13,830
And you thought I felt relieved to do so.

629
00:40:13,830 --> 00:40:15,010
Did you not?

630
00:40:15,010 --> 00:40:17,070
I didn't.

631
00:40:17,070 --> 00:40:22,140
- And let me explain another thing.
- He figured it out.

632
00:40:22,140 --> 00:40:25,070
I talked about attraction for a person
versus a romantic partner.

633
00:40:25,070 --> 00:40:30,760
I didn't mean to say it the way I did.

634
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:35,950
I thought you were trying
not to give me false hope.

635
00:40:35,950 --> 00:40:37,810
No, I wasn't.

636
00:40:37,810 --> 00:40:43,630
I kept wondering
why you texted me and all that.

637
00:40:43,630 --> 00:40:45,390
As for me...

638
00:40:45,390 --> 00:40:48,570
I didn't think of it
as drawing a line at all.

639
00:40:48,570 --> 00:40:50,220
Of course not.

640
00:40:50,220 --> 00:40:55,360
Were you just talking about the
two kinds of attractions, then?

641
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:58,600
Because you came to a realization?

642
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:01,210
I don't know why. I'm not
asking you to understand.

643
00:41:01,210 --> 00:41:03,420
I just wanted to tell you because it was you.

644
00:41:03,420 --> 00:41:06,280
I wasn't drawing a line. You know?

645
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:09,430
It's because we've talked
about that kind of stuff.

646
00:41:09,430 --> 00:41:11,730
Of course, I wasn't saying
you weren't the one.

647
00:41:11,730 --> 00:41:13,480
I'll have to be out of my mind.

648
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:16,910
I was saying you're a great person.

649
00:41:16,910 --> 00:41:19,360
I wasn't trying to draw a line.

650
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:24,650
I was trying to say I feel comfortable
and enjoy being with you.

651
00:41:24,650 --> 00:41:27,310
I think that was a misunderstanding.

652
00:41:27,310 --> 00:41:30,170
I wanted to resolve it quickly.

653
00:41:33,670 --> 00:41:37,660
I was upset because I felt like
I was your problem.

654
00:41:37,660 --> 00:41:40,370
- That's how I understood it.
- Right.

655
00:41:40,370 --> 00:41:42,970
Without realizing this,

656
00:41:42,970 --> 00:41:47,920
I kept wondering what went wrong.

657
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:51,300
I was really worried.

658
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:54,260
I think it's a relief now.

659
00:41:54,260 --> 00:41:57,500
While drinking whiskey downstairs,

660
00:41:57,500 --> 00:42:01,430
- I wasn't able to approach you.
- I know. Me, too.

661
00:42:01,430 --> 00:42:03,270
I couldn't approach you.

662
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:10,060
So, it's a relief that things got resolved.

663
00:42:11,180 --> 00:42:15,260
I'm sorry I let it out on you like that.

664
00:42:15,260 --> 00:42:18,420
- You must have felt flustered.
- No, no.

665
00:42:18,420 --> 00:42:21,840
- You must have felt stressed all day, too.
- No, no.

666
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:25,200
- Looks like Min Ju still likes him.
- I feel so relieved now.

667
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:27,270
Yes, I do, too.

668
00:42:27,270 --> 00:42:30,790
- It's such a relief.
- I know.

669
00:42:30,790 --> 00:42:35,140
[Things are getting untangled a bit tonight]

670
00:42:35,140 --> 00:42:37,530
I had no idea this would happen.

671
00:42:37,530 --> 00:42:40,120
When he talked to Min Ju about attraction

672
00:42:40,120 --> 00:42:43,070
for a person versus a romantic partner,

673
00:42:43,070 --> 00:42:49,000
he didn't mean he wasn't attracted
to her as a romantic partner.

674
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:51,450
He wasn't trying to draw the line
between them.

675
00:42:51,450 --> 00:42:54,240
I think it's so strange that
Min Ju was convinced.

676
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:57,250
- I don't get it! What's he talking about?
- Because she likes him.

677
00:42:57,250 --> 00:42:59,500
I'd be like, "What?

678
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:02,890
What does that mean?" Let's be honest.

679
00:43:02,890 --> 00:43:08,450
There are no words that could
have completely convinced her.

680
00:43:08,450 --> 00:43:10,980
It could've hurt her less...

681
00:43:10,980 --> 00:43:13,890
But it doesn't matter.
She likes him too much.

682
00:43:13,890 --> 00:43:16,540
I really want Min Ju to be happy.

683
00:43:16,540 --> 00:43:19,890
[That night]

684
00:43:19,890 --> 00:43:22,110
We got a message.

685
00:43:22,110 --> 00:43:24,510
[The letters from the women arrived]

686
00:43:24,510 --> 00:43:26,560
[Choose the letter and your last date]

687
00:43:26,560 --> 00:43:29,660
Are the men choosing their dates?

688
00:43:39,016 --> 00:43:43,780
[The letters from the women
are in front of them]

689
00:43:43,780 --> 00:43:45,960
[A month full of love, and left
with various feelings at the end]

690
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:48,960
- When did a month pass?
- A lot has happened.

691
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:53,040
[Excitement]

692
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:58,960
[Joy]

693
00:43:59,730 --> 00:44:02,090
[Jealousy]

694
00:44:02,090 --> 00:44:05,870
I fell for him too quickly.

695
00:44:05,870 --> 00:44:07,800
So, do you feel comfortable right now?

696
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:12,530
[Disappointment]

697
00:44:13,790 --> 00:44:18,088
[And...]

698
00:44:18,088 --> 00:44:21,518
What am I afraid of
before I start a relationship?

699
00:44:22,310 --> 00:44:28,780
[What are you afraid of
before you start a relationship?]

700
00:44:29,690 --> 00:44:32,950
I trust the other person too much.

701
00:44:32,950 --> 00:44:35,390
I want to trust them.

702
00:44:35,390 --> 00:44:40,400
How sincere are their feelings for me?

703
00:44:40,400 --> 00:44:45,080
Can I embrace those sides, too?

704
00:44:45,080 --> 00:44:48,320
I think I tend to be afraid of that.

705
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:50,340
[The tenants candidly
talked about their fears]

706
00:44:51,360 --> 00:44:58,220
[They wrote sincere letters to two men]

707
00:44:58,220 --> 00:45:00,650
Two men?

708
00:45:05,860 --> 00:45:07,140
[Anonymous letters]

709
00:45:07,140 --> 00:45:10,170
- They are anonymous?
- They choose only based on the letter?

710
00:45:10,170 --> 00:45:13,640
The women sent the letters
to specific people.

711
00:45:13,640 --> 00:45:16,080
But they don't say who they're from.

712
00:45:17,130 --> 00:45:22,230
[Can they tell who wrote it
based on the sentiment?]

713
00:45:22,230 --> 00:45:24,220
Gosh, this is crazy.

714
00:45:24,930 --> 00:45:26,330
[I'm afraid to get hurt in a relationship]

715
00:45:26,330 --> 00:45:30,210
"I'm afraid to get hurt in a relationship."

716
00:45:30,210 --> 00:45:31,950
That's Min Ju.

717
00:45:32,760 --> 00:45:35,460
I move on...

718
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:41,080
if I feel like I'm going to get hurt.

719
00:45:41,080 --> 00:45:46,000
I think that was a way to protect myself.

720
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:51,610
When I feel like
I'm the only one who's sincere,

721
00:45:51,610 --> 00:45:54,630
I try not to fall too deep.

722
00:45:54,630 --> 00:45:57,730
Because I don't want to get hurt,
to be honest.

723
00:45:58,670 --> 00:46:01,930
[Can Seong Min guess who wrote the letter?]

724
00:46:03,100 --> 00:46:04,130
[The letter Seo Won received]

725
00:46:04,130 --> 00:46:05,770
What about Seo Won?

726
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:09,790
Whoa, he got three.

727
00:46:09,790 --> 00:46:12,350
[Are their feelings sincere?
Will our feelings grow at the same rate?]

728
00:46:12,350 --> 00:46:19,410
In order to not fall too deep,

729
00:46:19,410 --> 00:46:23,740
I tend to be cautious at first out of fear.

730
00:46:23,740 --> 00:46:27,910
Because I don't want to
fall apart if I fall too deep.

731
00:46:30,820 --> 00:46:34,640
"I'm afraid to show my ugly side."
Who's that?

732
00:46:35,430 --> 00:46:37,550
I tend to...

733
00:46:38,660 --> 00:46:41,570
try to hide a side of me

734
00:46:41,570 --> 00:46:46,570
I'm embarrassed about from other people.

735
00:46:46,570 --> 00:46:49,530
Whether it's something positive
or something you want to hide,

736
00:46:49,530 --> 00:46:53,070
you express yourself honestly.

737
00:46:54,170 --> 00:46:56,670
I thought that was very manly.

738
00:46:57,882 --> 00:47:03,792
[Did Seo Won figure out
who wrote the letters?]

739
00:47:04,950 --> 00:47:07,860
I know exactly who wrote them.

740
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:11,320
Why is it so hard to choose?

741
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:13,290
He doesn't know who to go on a date with.

742
00:47:13,290 --> 00:47:16,340
[Jun Hyeon received two letters]

743
00:47:16,340 --> 00:47:19,400
[And Wu Yeol...]

744
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:22,990
I trust the other person too much.

745
00:47:22,990 --> 00:47:25,900
- I want to trust them.
- Yu Gyeong.

746
00:47:25,900 --> 00:47:29,160
And I want their trust.

747
00:47:29,160 --> 00:47:31,340
If they trust me,

748
00:47:31,340 --> 00:47:36,460
I'm willing to do anything.

749
00:47:36,460 --> 00:47:44,630
That's why I always choose
that path despite my fear.

750
00:47:44,630 --> 00:47:48,410
Right. That's a good thing.

751
00:47:48,410 --> 00:47:52,450
When I gave the letters to the two men,

752
00:47:52,450 --> 00:47:55,280
I was sure that Jun Hyeon would know.

753
00:47:55,280 --> 00:47:57,740
Looks like she trusts him.

754
00:47:57,740 --> 00:48:01,140
But I wondered if Wu Yeol would know.

755
00:48:01,140 --> 00:48:04,140
Was he able to see me?

756
00:48:04,140 --> 00:48:06,800
Does he know me well?

757
00:48:06,800 --> 00:48:12,050
I wondered if he would recognize
me and come to me.

758
00:48:12,860 --> 00:48:15,020
I tend to trust people easily.

759
00:48:15,020 --> 00:48:23,360
That's why I feel betrayed
and hurt from that, too.

760
00:48:23,360 --> 00:48:26,470
[Jun Hyeon is reading the pink letter]

761
00:48:27,190 --> 00:48:28,670
[Wu Yeol is holding a purple letter]

762
00:48:28,670 --> 00:48:30,910
- Purple one is...
- Who's that?

763
00:48:33,190 --> 00:48:39,230
How sincere are their feelings for me?

764
00:48:39,230 --> 00:48:43,480
Will our feelings grow at the same rate?

765
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:48,830
I think I tend to be most afraid of that.

766
00:48:50,840 --> 00:48:52,150
[Putting it down]

767
00:48:52,150 --> 00:48:55,200
What do we do?

768
00:48:55,200 --> 00:48:57,860
I hope he guesses both correctly.

769
00:48:59,960 --> 00:49:01,140
[Will they know who wrote these letters?]

770
00:49:01,140 --> 00:49:03,810
I think the theme of this season is fear.

771
00:49:03,810 --> 00:49:06,350
It's because they're sincere.

772
00:49:08,630 --> 00:49:10,770
How do we decide on this?

773
00:49:12,640 --> 00:49:14,930
Don't you think it's easy to tell?

774
00:49:18,340 --> 00:49:19,850
It is.

775
00:49:22,370 --> 00:49:24,740
First of all,

776
00:49:24,740 --> 00:49:28,880
should we put the person we want on top?

777
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:33,600
- For now?
- We should chat if we overlap.

778
00:49:35,440 --> 00:49:38,580
Seo Won gets to choose because
he got the most letters.

779
00:49:38,580 --> 00:49:41,400
- Can I think about it a little more?
- Go ahead.

780
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:44,840
- You have to think it through.
- Because it's important.

781
00:49:50,750 --> 00:49:52,890
Are you done deciding, Hyung?

782
00:49:52,890 --> 00:49:54,240
Yes.

783
00:50:03,170 --> 00:50:05,560
Why am I so torn?

784
00:50:06,790 --> 00:50:09,250
[A few days ago]

785
00:50:09,250 --> 00:50:15,690
[He struggled
to choose his official date, too]

786
00:50:15,690 --> 00:50:19,680
He's that torn between Gyu Ri and So Yun?

787
00:50:21,710 --> 00:50:29,660
[He hesitated for a while]

788
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:33,300
Gosh.

789
00:50:33,300 --> 00:50:36,820
- Why are things so hard here?
- Goodness.

790
00:50:38,430 --> 00:50:43,360
[He burst into tears]

791
00:50:43,950 --> 00:50:46,660
[He is hesitating to make the
decision again today]

792
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:53,080
[Their fate will be decided
based on Seo Won's decision]

793
00:50:54,880 --> 00:50:58,390
[Since Seo Won gets to choose first]

794
00:50:58,390 --> 00:51:03,940
[They will get to go on a date
with someone he doesn't choose]

795
00:51:03,940 --> 00:51:06,190
I can't look.

796
00:51:06,190 --> 00:51:09,480
Seo Won's face got red.

797
00:51:09,480 --> 00:51:11,300
[He's delaying his decision]

798
00:51:11,300 --> 00:51:15,410
This means his feelings for So Yun
are as strong.

799
00:51:17,430 --> 00:51:18,850
I...

800
00:51:21,370 --> 00:51:23,190
choose the pink one.

801
00:51:23,190 --> 00:51:24,910
[Jun Hyeon chose Yu Gyeong's letter]

802
00:51:24,910 --> 00:51:27,120
Yu Gyeong, okay.

803
00:51:27,120 --> 00:51:30,330
[Jun Hyeon chose Yu Gyeong's letter]

804
00:51:32,160 --> 00:51:36,700
[What will Wu Yeol choose?]

805
00:51:40,290 --> 00:51:44,340
I... I read the letters...

806
00:51:45,350 --> 00:51:48,810
and knew who wrote them immediately.

807
00:51:54,120 --> 00:51:55,940
I choose the pink one.

808
00:51:57,090 --> 00:52:04,150
[He knew it was from Yu Gyeong immediately]

809
00:52:07,810 --> 00:52:12,050
[Wu Yeol also chooses the pink one]

810
00:52:12,050 --> 00:52:13,810
[They chose the same letter]

811
00:52:13,810 --> 00:52:15,930
He can't hide his feelings.

812
00:52:17,830 --> 00:52:22,250
[The ball is in Seo Won's court]

813
00:52:22,250 --> 00:52:24,650
I debated a lot after reading the letters.

814
00:52:25,470 --> 00:52:30,200
[Who will end up with whom
on their last date?]

815
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:31,550
This is hard.

816
00:52:31,550 --> 00:52:35,160
Seo Won is so tormented.

817
00:52:35,160 --> 00:52:36,440
He even cried.

818
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:44,570
For the first time, I realized
how torn and tormented he was

819
00:52:44,570 --> 00:52:47,480
between Gyu Ri and So Yun.

820
00:52:47,480 --> 00:52:51,640
Neither Jun Hyeon nor Wu Yeol
has a reason to back down.

821
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:54,870
- None at all.
- They both like Yu Gyeong a lot.

822
00:52:54,870 --> 00:52:58,650
Right now, they are not backing down.

823
00:52:58,650 --> 00:53:01,350
They need to have
the last date with Yu Gyeong.

824
00:53:01,350 --> 00:53:04,540
The last date must have
a big impact on their decision, right?

825
00:53:04,540 --> 00:53:06,730
Of course. Of course.

826
00:53:06,730 --> 00:53:09,370
It could be a poison or a blessing.

827
00:53:09,370 --> 00:53:11,690
They have one day left.

828
00:53:12,690 --> 00:53:15,440
- What happened?
- This is crazy.

829
00:53:15,440 --> 00:53:18,630
[The morning of their last date is here]

830
00:53:20,880 --> 00:53:22,630
Seong Min?

831
00:53:25,430 --> 00:53:27,440
Seong Min.

832
00:53:27,440 --> 00:53:33,750
[Waiting for his trip partner,
looking nervous]

833
00:53:34,910 --> 00:53:39,370
[Reading the letter again]

834
00:53:42,860 --> 00:53:50,000
[Will the person he wanted come?]

835
00:53:53,060 --> 00:53:54,430
Gosh, it's Min Ju.

836
00:53:54,430 --> 00:53:56,630
This is so funny.

837
00:53:59,090 --> 00:54:00,880
Hi.

838
00:54:02,860 --> 00:54:04,510
When did you get here?

839
00:54:04,510 --> 00:54:06,520
- Just now.
- Just now?

840
00:54:06,520 --> 00:54:09,110
- It's so windy here.
- It is.

841
00:54:09,110 --> 00:54:11,330
Namsan Park.

842
00:54:12,290 --> 00:54:14,470
It was you.

843
00:54:14,470 --> 00:54:16,180
It was me.

844
00:54:18,230 --> 00:54:21,830
I just knew it was you.

845
00:54:21,830 --> 00:54:24,190
- Really?
- So nice.

846
00:54:24,190 --> 00:54:26,210
The weather's nice, too.

847
00:54:26,210 --> 00:54:29,090
The weather is ridiculously good.

848
00:54:30,340 --> 00:54:32,780
Did you sleep well after our chat last night?

849
00:54:32,780 --> 00:54:34,310
Pretty much.

850
00:54:35,310 --> 00:54:40,030
- Did you not sleep?
- I slept well. I felt relieved, too.

851
00:54:41,120 --> 00:54:44,760
We had a misunderstanding.

852
00:54:44,760 --> 00:54:50,080
We had many thoughts
over the past three weeks.

853
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:53,800
Let's forget about everything
and have fun today.

854
00:54:53,800 --> 00:54:58,420
Do I have to play a clown again?

855
00:54:58,420 --> 00:55:00,560
Should I make you laugh all day?

856
00:55:00,560 --> 00:55:02,700
- I'll make you laugh all day.
- I love it.

857
00:55:02,700 --> 00:55:05,490
I hope they have a nice day.

858
00:55:05,490 --> 00:55:12,490
At first, I want to do more
because it's the last day.

859
00:55:12,490 --> 00:55:14,960
But after giving it some thought...

860
00:55:14,960 --> 00:55:17,210
I need to stop thinking.
Why do I think so much?

861
00:55:17,210 --> 00:55:20,240
I always talk about thinking. I need to stop.

862
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:27,100
You think a lot, but your actions
don't seem that wise.

863
00:55:27,100 --> 00:55:28,810
You're right, Min Ju.

864
00:55:28,810 --> 00:55:31,300
Compared to how much you think.

865
00:55:32,110 --> 00:55:33,970
I just think a lot.

866
00:55:33,970 --> 00:55:37,480
[Time to stop thinking
and enjoy the last trip]

867
00:55:38,820 --> 00:55:42,510
There's an arboretum and a park.

868
00:55:42,510 --> 00:55:47,020
- Let's do something really fun.
- We've checked out stuff a lot.

869
00:55:47,020 --> 00:55:48,700
Do you like to exercise?

870
00:55:48,700 --> 00:55:51,720
- You seem like you enjoy being active.
- I do.

871
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:56,450
[Min Ju mentioned
that she enjoys being active]

872
00:55:57,600 --> 00:55:59,600
[Thinking]

873
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:02,770
- Something active and dopamine-spiking?
- I love it.

874
00:56:02,770 --> 00:56:06,160
- Like a mud festival or something.
- I love stuff like that.

875
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:08,650
- Oppa.
- Zipline?

876
00:56:08,650 --> 00:56:14,090
I thought about this.
I was wondering if they had this.

877
00:56:14,090 --> 00:56:16,280
- You said you like it.
- I love it.

878
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:19,030
I've never flown in the air.

879
00:56:19,030 --> 00:56:22,060
It suddenly feels like we're going on a trip.

880
00:56:22,060 --> 00:56:24,460
- Suddenly?
- I'm so excited!

881
00:56:24,460 --> 00:56:27,480
[Arrived at the destination feeling excited]

882
00:56:28,380 --> 00:56:32,450
[Wearing cute helmets together]

883
00:56:32,450 --> 00:56:34,720
We'll wave when I lower the phone.

884
00:56:34,720 --> 00:56:37,400
One, two, three.

885
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:38,980
So cute.

886
00:56:38,980 --> 00:56:41,730
[Hi, ladybug couple]

887
00:56:41,730 --> 00:56:45,560
- Hello.
- Your hair is so stubborn.

888
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:47,230
I need to hold it.

889
00:56:47,230 --> 00:56:49,710
- This is nice.
- What's going on?

890
00:56:49,710 --> 00:56:51,180
Isn't it?

891
00:56:51,180 --> 00:56:55,500
- This hair is stubborn, too.
- It keeps trying to go into my mouth.

892
00:56:57,380 --> 00:56:58,450
[Smiling]

893
00:57:00,080 --> 00:57:02,830
- How far are we going up?
- How far are we going up?

894
00:57:02,830 --> 00:57:05,100
How far are we going up?

895
00:57:06,730 --> 00:57:10,310
It's scary. I haven't done stuff like this
in a while.

896
00:57:10,310 --> 00:57:12,120
Me, neither.

897
00:57:12,120 --> 00:57:16,870
- I'm scared.
- Hold on, I'm not ready yet.

898
00:57:16,870 --> 00:57:20,130
- Hold on.
- We'll be landing over there.

899
00:57:21,590 --> 00:57:24,700
- We are landing from here to there.
- They'll be crossing the ocean.

900
00:57:24,700 --> 00:57:27,350
- This is the kind of thing I wanted to do.
- Stuff like this?

901
00:57:27,350 --> 00:57:29,500
We never got to do stuff like this.

902
00:57:29,500 --> 00:57:33,840
- They'll suddenly push us.
- We look funny holding it like this.

903
00:57:37,140 --> 00:57:40,780
- That looks fun.
- It looks so fun.

904
00:57:40,780 --> 00:57:42,310
So pretty.

905
00:57:43,180 --> 00:57:48,710
[They are crossing the ocean]

906
00:57:50,724 --> 00:57:52,399
How fun.

907
00:57:52,399 --> 00:57:57,520
- A thrilling activity like that is memorable.
- Right.

908
00:57:57,520 --> 00:58:01,370
- Wow, look at the waves.
- The sun is setting right now.

909
00:58:01,370 --> 00:58:03,430
Let's take a photo quickly.

910
00:58:04,710 --> 00:58:06,560
They make a nice couple.

911
00:58:08,750 --> 00:58:11,070
- It looks nice.
- Does it?

912
00:58:11,070 --> 00:58:14,550
The song "Hollywood" should
be the background music.

913
00:58:14,550 --> 00:58:16,560
The Black Skirts' "Hollywood"
should play in the background.

914
00:58:16,560 --> 00:58:19,060
[It's like she's in a music video]

915
00:58:19,060 --> 00:58:20,040
So cute.

916
00:58:20,040 --> 00:58:21,540
Oppa.

917
00:58:23,660 --> 00:58:26,600
So pretty. It looks nice.

918
00:58:26,600 --> 00:58:27,940
So pretty.

919
00:58:28,780 --> 00:58:30,400
This is pretty, too.

920
00:58:30,400 --> 00:58:34,520
Seong Min Ju.

921
00:58:35,480 --> 00:58:38,350
- Isn't this cute?
- Wow. Totally.

922
00:58:39,640 --> 00:58:41,640
So pretty.

923
00:58:43,280 --> 00:58:46,470
I'll never forget this song.

924
00:58:46,470 --> 00:58:48,410
Just start dating.

925
00:58:52,070 --> 00:58:54,980
[Their last trip]

926
00:58:54,980 --> 00:58:58,410
How could she have such
a strong feeling for one person?

927
00:58:58,410 --> 00:59:00,530
She fell for him.

928
00:59:00,530 --> 00:59:04,100
Min Ju seems to have fun with Seong Min.

929
00:59:04,100 --> 00:59:06,350
Time goes by quickly, too.

930
00:59:06,350 --> 00:59:10,230
She said that's the most
important thing to her.

931
00:59:11,190 --> 00:59:12,350
[Wow]

932
00:59:12,350 --> 00:59:13,720
What's this?

933
00:59:13,720 --> 00:59:15,730
This is so nice.

934
00:59:15,730 --> 00:59:17,460
Nice.

935
00:59:17,460 --> 00:59:21,440
It's kind of like a campsite.

936
00:59:22,850 --> 00:59:24,420
So pretty.

937
00:59:25,440 --> 00:59:28,050
- You look a bit...
- Is my face too red?

938
00:59:28,050 --> 00:59:29,760
You're transformed.

939
00:59:29,760 --> 00:59:32,160
[Noticing the touch-up makeup]

940
00:59:32,930 --> 00:59:34,830
I transformed.

941
00:59:35,570 --> 00:59:37,570
- This is interesting.
- So cute.

942
00:59:42,310 --> 00:59:44,900
Are you cold at all? Do you have this?

943
00:59:44,900 --> 00:59:47,500
- Are you wearing it?
- I have it here.

944
00:59:47,500 --> 00:59:50,990
- I should carry it.
- He's attentive.

945
00:59:53,450 --> 00:59:54,960
[Fireworks outside the window]

946
00:59:54,960 --> 00:59:57,070
Fireworks.

947
00:59:57,940 --> 00:59:59,700
[Stumbled upon fireworks at the beach]

948
00:59:59,700 --> 01:00:01,580
Fireworks?

949
01:00:03,730 --> 01:00:05,350
[Staring]

950
01:00:07,140 --> 01:00:10,960
- Remember our fireworks?
- I do. On our last night in Tokushima.

951
01:00:10,960 --> 01:00:14,260
I remember sticking with you then.

952
01:00:14,260 --> 01:00:16,800
While playing with fireworks.

953
01:00:16,800 --> 01:00:18,480
[Last night in Tokushima]

954
01:00:18,480 --> 01:00:20,700
What? Hold this.

955
01:00:21,600 --> 01:00:24,540
Min Ju's brakes are broken.

956
01:00:24,540 --> 01:00:26,580
Here. Take one each.

957
01:00:26,580 --> 01:00:28,330
This is like a fire.

958
01:00:28,330 --> 01:00:31,940
Shake something. Shake something.

959
01:00:33,620 --> 01:00:35,770
We had an all-day date then.

960
01:00:35,770 --> 01:00:38,340
Right, we had a date all day.

961
01:00:42,610 --> 01:00:46,210
I hope this moment lasts forever.

962
01:00:46,210 --> 01:00:49,760
I struggle to say stuff like that.
I usually don't like to.

963
01:00:49,760 --> 01:00:52,690
But I'm working off my courage now.

964
01:00:52,690 --> 01:00:56,160
I'm starting to feel comfortable. It's nice.

965
01:00:57,100 --> 01:00:59,350
[Moved]

966
01:01:04,690 --> 01:01:07,900
- Gosh.
- It must be so memorable.

967
01:01:07,900 --> 01:01:09,440
Really.

968
01:01:13,150 --> 01:01:18,740
I had all sorts of emotions here. All sorts.

969
01:01:19,800 --> 01:01:23,510
[Staring]

970
01:01:24,070 --> 01:01:28,720
Do you have any regrets at this point?

971
01:01:29,840 --> 01:01:32,430
I thought about what I regret.

972
01:01:42,910 --> 01:01:46,850
The fact that I hurt you unintentionally.

973
01:01:46,850 --> 01:01:53,320
I'm thinking I must have done it many times.

974
01:01:53,320 --> 01:01:56,090
You have. But he's admitting it.

975
01:01:57,350 --> 01:02:01,350
I thought I was mature at first.

976
01:02:01,350 --> 01:02:04,570
- You thought you were doing well.
- I'm older, too.

977
01:02:04,570 --> 01:02:10,420
I thought I was solid,
thoughtful, and put together.

978
01:02:11,680 --> 01:02:18,440
I thought I could do things
intentionally, but I can't.

979
01:02:18,440 --> 01:02:20,380
I didn't realize it, but...

980
01:02:22,710 --> 01:02:24,890
I was just a kid, too.

981
01:02:24,890 --> 01:02:27,820
I realized how immature I am.

982
01:02:27,820 --> 01:02:31,210
I'm so immature and clumsy.

983
01:02:31,210 --> 01:02:35,540
I'm so near-sighted, and I've been selfish.

984
01:02:35,540 --> 01:02:40,320
I thought I was very thoughtful of others.

985
01:02:40,320 --> 01:02:44,850
But I realized I was selfish in the end.

986
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:51,030
We've talked a lot, but we don't
know each other well enough.

987
01:02:51,030 --> 01:02:53,750
The way we communicate is very different.

988
01:02:53,750 --> 01:02:56,570
- Our thoughts...
- They're different.

989
01:02:56,570 --> 01:03:00,010
- Our thought process...
- The way we think is very different.

990
01:03:00,010 --> 01:03:03,150
- It's very different.
- I don't keep a journal, Oppa.

991
01:03:03,150 --> 01:03:05,280
I know.

992
01:03:05,280 --> 01:03:06,710
Seriously.

993
01:03:07,390 --> 01:03:11,250
But we still found it easy
to talk to each other.

994
01:03:11,250 --> 01:03:14,590
I think it's because you've
been considerate of me.

995
01:03:14,590 --> 01:03:18,130
Not at all. I can tell you are trying, too.

996
01:03:18,130 --> 01:03:21,810
You try to communicate well.

997
01:03:22,600 --> 01:03:25,560
I have to. I have to.

998
01:03:25,560 --> 01:03:29,770
- Although a lot has happened...
- Right.

999
01:03:34,870 --> 01:03:38,570
- Do you feel at ease?
- I won't say that so easily.

1000
01:03:38,570 --> 01:03:41,240
I'll stop saying that from now on.

1001
01:03:43,720 --> 01:03:48,540
- I can't believe this is the end.
- I can't, either.

1002
01:03:48,540 --> 01:03:54,690
The last three weeks have
been an emotional roller coaster.

1003
01:03:55,690 --> 01:03:58,520
- It was crazy.
- It was.

1004
01:04:01,550 --> 01:04:04,360
- I don't feel so great.
- Why?

1005
01:04:05,070 --> 01:04:10,750
Because I was stressed, I didn't
realize you were stressed about me.

1006
01:04:13,780 --> 01:04:18,850
You had your feelings, but I was confused.

1007
01:04:18,850 --> 01:04:21,500
I didn't know what to do in that moment.

1008
01:04:21,500 --> 01:04:25,640
I couldn't say that earlier.
That's what I regret.

1009
01:04:25,640 --> 01:04:27,740
I see.

1010
01:04:29,190 --> 01:04:32,290
I have to admit something.

1011
01:04:33,010 --> 01:04:36,560
- I think I've been driving 200 km/h.
- Right.

1012
01:04:36,560 --> 01:04:43,170
I should have tried to brake consciously.

1013
01:04:43,170 --> 01:04:46,950
But I'm not capable of doing that.

1014
01:04:46,950 --> 01:04:48,800
I think that was a struggle.

1015
01:04:48,800 --> 01:04:50,410
I was affected by every little thing.

1016
01:04:50,410 --> 01:04:53,180
I felt crushed by a comment.

1017
01:04:53,180 --> 01:04:56,320
And a comment made me feel happy, too.

1018
01:04:56,320 --> 01:04:59,930
But there's one thing I've been
meaning to tell you.

1019
01:04:59,930 --> 01:05:02,810
I was so grateful that you were here.

1020
01:05:02,810 --> 01:05:08,080
And I'm grateful that you let me
experience this emotional roller coaster.

1021
01:05:08,080 --> 01:05:10,170
She won't be able to feel that again.

1022
01:05:10,170 --> 01:05:11,610
I feel the same.

1023
01:05:11,610 --> 01:05:14,600
While I was here,

1024
01:05:14,600 --> 01:05:18,430
I relied on you emotionally a lot.

1025
01:05:18,430 --> 01:05:21,760
I'm so grateful. Even now.

1026
01:05:21,760 --> 01:05:23,800
And probably tomorrow, too.

1027
01:05:25,180 --> 01:05:32,560
[A night with lasting emotions]

1028
01:05:32,560 --> 01:05:34,060
She still likes him.

1029
01:05:34,060 --> 01:05:36,760
Seong Min is so blessed.

1030
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:38,940
The fact that someone likes him,
no matter what.

1031
01:05:38,940 --> 01:05:42,060
She can't step on the brake
because she likes him.

1032
01:05:42,060 --> 01:05:46,260
So, do you think Seong Min
will choose Min Ju?

1033
01:05:46,260 --> 01:05:48,430
- I think he might.
- I think he might.

1034
01:05:48,430 --> 01:05:51,370
We saw her angry for the first time.

1035
01:05:51,370 --> 01:05:55,360
She always smiled in front of you,
but she suddenly changed.

1036
01:05:55,360 --> 01:05:57,490
That apparently could make you fall for her.

1037
01:05:57,490 --> 01:05:59,620
There was a study in England or something.

1038
01:05:59,620 --> 01:06:01,980
It happens. It happens.

1039
01:06:01,980 --> 01:06:05,210
It definitely had an impact on him.

1040
01:06:05,210 --> 01:06:07,820
Heart pounding.

1041
01:06:09,100 --> 01:06:12,280
[Wu Yeol is waiting for his date]

1042
01:06:12,280 --> 01:06:16,150
It's Wu Yeol. What's important
is who his date is.

1043
01:06:16,150 --> 01:06:19,200
- That color is...
- Is it Gyu Ri or Yu Gyeong?

1044
01:06:19,200 --> 01:06:20,800
[Who is the owner of the letter?]

1045
01:06:31,850 --> 01:06:33,950
Huh? Hold on. Hold on.

1046
01:06:33,950 --> 01:06:37,230
[Is it the person he expects?]

1047
01:06:37,230 --> 01:06:41,320
[Excited and nervous]

1048
01:06:47,750 --> 01:06:49,560
- It's Yu Gyeong.
- Oppa.

1049
01:06:49,560 --> 01:06:52,110
It's Yu Gyeong!

1050
01:06:56,340 --> 01:06:57,990
[All smiles]

1051
01:07:00,260 --> 01:07:01,780
[Wu Yeol's date is Yu Gyeong]

1052
01:07:01,780 --> 01:07:03,560
So pretty.

1053
01:07:05,200 --> 01:07:07,260
He must be excited.

1054
01:07:08,390 --> 01:07:10,490
She dressed so prettily.

1055
01:07:10,490 --> 01:07:14,870
Long time no see. That's my letter.

1056
01:07:18,660 --> 01:07:20,910
What's up with his look?

1057
01:07:25,120 --> 01:07:26,800
It's funny to see you like this.

1058
01:07:26,800 --> 01:07:28,750
- What's the deal?
- What?

1059
01:07:28,750 --> 01:07:31,000
It's mine...

1060
01:07:31,000 --> 01:07:32,500
What did you say?

1061
01:07:33,240 --> 01:07:35,240
[Yu Gyeong is feeling shy]

1062
01:07:35,240 --> 01:07:39,960
- What's the deal?
- She's most adorable when she's with him.

1063
01:07:40,870 --> 01:07:43,200
I'm embarrassed.

1064
01:07:44,780 --> 01:07:47,350
- I knew it was you immediately.
- Really?

1065
01:07:47,350 --> 01:07:49,600
He knew right away.

1066
01:07:51,090 --> 01:07:56,180
[He knew it was from Yu Gyeong immediately]

1067
01:07:56,180 --> 01:07:57,660
Yu Gyeong.

1068
01:07:58,660 --> 01:08:00,820
I knew right away.

1069
01:08:00,820 --> 01:08:02,180
Really?

1070
01:08:02,900 --> 01:08:07,330
I had my doubts. I wasn't sure
if you'd recognize me.

1071
01:08:07,330 --> 01:08:11,020
Of course I did. How could I not?

1072
01:08:11,020 --> 01:08:12,740
The last four lines.

1073
01:08:12,740 --> 01:08:15,340
She can do anything
if someone earns her trust.

1074
01:08:15,340 --> 01:08:16,990
- Did it sound like me?
- Yes.

1075
01:08:16,990 --> 01:08:18,410
Really?

1076
01:08:18,410 --> 01:08:21,240
- My gosh.
- It's so romantic.

1077
01:08:25,320 --> 01:08:26,850
Are you embarrassed?

1078
01:08:28,510 --> 01:08:31,270
Yes, I'm so embarrassed.

1079
01:08:34,710 --> 01:08:36,750
You look pretty today.

1080
01:08:37,860 --> 01:08:39,840
You seem to know a bit about me.

1081
01:08:39,840 --> 01:08:41,870
I do now.

1082
01:08:41,870 --> 01:08:44,280
Even I feel good.

1083
01:08:46,770 --> 01:08:51,040
I'm wearing leather because
I knew it would be you.

1084
01:08:51,040 --> 01:08:52,970
I carried this with me.

1085
01:08:52,970 --> 01:08:55,460
- They're so cute.
- I'm surprised by your outfit today.

1086
01:08:55,460 --> 01:08:57,440
Really? It's a bit different, isn't it?

1087
01:08:57,440 --> 01:08:59,390
Yes. I like that style.

1088
01:08:59,390 --> 01:09:00,210
Really?

1089
01:09:00,210 --> 01:09:02,220
I think he has a crush on her.

1090
01:09:02,220 --> 01:09:04,040
It suits you well.

1091
01:09:04,040 --> 01:09:05,330
Thank you.

1092
01:09:05,330 --> 01:09:07,580
You look good, too.

1093
01:09:09,820 --> 01:09:12,640
The weather is so nice today.

1094
01:09:17,600 --> 01:09:20,950
[Wu Yeol is blocking the sun for her]

1095
01:09:20,950 --> 01:09:23,700
- Do you know about Gunsan?
- Gunsan?

1096
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:26,860
- It's below Seoul.
- Probably below.

1097
01:09:26,860 --> 01:09:29,530
- Probably not above.
- Not above.

1098
01:09:29,530 --> 01:09:31,210
- Are we driving there?
- We are.

1099
01:09:31,210 --> 01:09:32,800
I see.

1100
01:09:37,360 --> 01:09:38,860
You look so different.

1101
01:09:38,860 --> 01:09:43,050
Really? I thought about doing a half-updo.

1102
01:09:43,050 --> 01:09:45,980
I think wearing it down suits the look today.

1103
01:09:45,980 --> 01:09:47,920
I thought it might be too much.

1104
01:09:47,920 --> 01:09:49,960
Do it some other time.

1105
01:09:49,960 --> 01:09:51,310
Some other time?

1106
01:09:51,310 --> 01:09:52,860
Shall we go?

1107
01:09:52,860 --> 01:09:54,360
Some other time, he said.

1108
01:09:54,360 --> 01:09:57,670
- Things are going the way I want.
- Really?

1109
01:09:57,670 --> 01:09:59,370
It's true.

1110
01:10:00,110 --> 01:10:03,560
If it wasn't you today,

1111
01:10:03,560 --> 01:10:06,200
I was going to go home. I mean it.

1112
01:10:06,200 --> 01:10:07,940
After checking who it is?

1113
01:10:08,950 --> 01:10:12,900
I knew it would be you.

1114
01:10:12,900 --> 01:10:16,620
- You said you weren't sure if I'd know.
- Of course.

1115
01:10:16,620 --> 01:10:19,100
I was just hoping.

1116
01:10:20,490 --> 01:10:21,830
You really want me to drive?

1117
01:10:21,830 --> 01:10:24,450
- Do you mean it?
- You mean driving?

1118
01:10:24,450 --> 01:10:26,550
- I'll show you.
- I'll sit next to you.

1119
01:10:26,550 --> 01:10:28,890
[Yu Gyeong is sitting in the driver's seat]

1120
01:10:28,890 --> 01:10:30,640
Gosh, Yu Gyeong is driving?

1121
01:10:30,640 --> 01:10:34,510
I haven't driven in a month,
just so you know.

1122
01:10:37,170 --> 01:10:38,710
Should I pull this forward for you?

1123
01:10:38,710 --> 01:10:40,490
- The seat?
- Yes.

1124
01:10:40,490 --> 01:10:41,930
What's this?

1125
01:10:41,930 --> 01:10:45,630
Hold on. Stop moving it.

1126
01:10:45,630 --> 01:10:49,370
My legs aren't that short.
They aren't much shorter than yours.

1127
01:10:49,370 --> 01:10:50,760
Does it feel comfortable?

1128
01:10:50,760 --> 01:10:52,610
- What about the back?
- It's good.

1129
01:10:52,610 --> 01:10:55,140
[Adjusting the rearview mirror]

1130
01:10:55,140 --> 01:10:57,070
You want to look at me?

1131
01:10:59,290 --> 01:11:01,200
[Practicing switching gears]

1132
01:11:02,100 --> 01:11:04,390
You are practicing switching to D?

1133
01:11:04,390 --> 01:11:06,410
I've never done it before.

1134
01:11:06,410 --> 01:11:08,910
I was joking. I thought it was cute.

1135
01:11:08,910 --> 01:11:11,330
The turn signal. The accelerator.

1136
01:11:11,330 --> 01:11:13,140
What is she, learning how to drive?

1137
01:11:13,140 --> 01:11:14,600
Should we go, then?

1138
01:11:14,600 --> 01:11:16,530
[Starting to feel nervous]

1139
01:11:17,150 --> 01:11:19,750
I'm so scared. I'm so nervous.

1140
01:11:19,750 --> 01:11:23,470
What if I get pulled over?
I want to hide from the police.

1141
01:11:23,470 --> 01:11:24,700
She's so cute.

1142
01:11:24,700 --> 01:11:26,430
He's here to arrest you.

1143
01:11:28,550 --> 01:11:31,290
- They won't stop laughing.
- Why is it so funny?

1144
01:11:32,570 --> 01:11:34,120
I'm doing great.

1145
01:11:35,040 --> 01:11:36,840
It's going well.

1146
01:11:38,140 --> 01:11:42,580
You might get seriously car sick.

1147
01:11:42,580 --> 01:11:45,470
- I like getting carsick.
- How could you possibly like it?

1148
01:11:45,470 --> 01:11:47,700
- I'll be happy, no matter what.
- Really?

1149
01:11:47,700 --> 01:11:50,200
I'll forgive you even if you suddenly brake.

1150
01:11:50,200 --> 01:11:52,310
Daebak.

1151
01:11:54,370 --> 01:11:57,250
You're actually better than I thought.

1152
01:11:57,250 --> 01:12:01,320
I'm not that clumsy a person.

1153
01:12:01,320 --> 01:12:04,130
- You surprised me.
- My gosh.

1154
01:12:04,130 --> 01:12:06,850
I'll make sure to drive safely.

1155
01:12:06,850 --> 01:12:08,150
Of course.

1156
01:12:08,150 --> 01:12:13,400
We don't want our next date
at an orthopedic's.

1157
01:12:13,400 --> 01:12:16,450
It could be worse than that.

1158
01:12:17,710 --> 01:12:22,130
I thought I would feel very nervous.

1159
01:12:22,130 --> 01:12:26,110
Before we met up, but...

1160
01:12:26,110 --> 01:12:28,070
I guess I was confident.

1161
01:12:28,070 --> 01:12:31,710
You knew you'd be seeing... Seeing me.

1162
01:12:31,710 --> 01:12:33,480
I can't speak.

1163
01:12:33,480 --> 01:12:37,800
I was confident that it would be you.

1164
01:12:38,630 --> 01:12:39,860
I was, too.

1165
01:12:39,860 --> 01:12:43,640
I knew it was you the moment
I saw the pink paper.

1166
01:12:44,460 --> 01:12:46,660
- You were able to see me?
- Yes.

1167
01:12:48,080 --> 01:12:50,780
I am grateful that you chose me.

1168
01:12:50,780 --> 01:12:53,000
I knew it was you the moment I read this.

1169
01:12:53,000 --> 01:12:54,890
[Even if I get hurt, I try to be honest
instead of being afraid]

1170
01:12:54,890 --> 01:12:56,500
Get hurt.

1171
01:12:56,500 --> 01:12:58,350
Have you been hurt?

1172
01:12:59,280 --> 01:13:01,920
- I have not.
- Really?

1173
01:13:02,820 --> 01:13:05,240
- I've been healed.
- Huh?

1174
01:13:05,240 --> 01:13:06,920
How?

1175
01:13:06,920 --> 01:13:09,200
Because you came to see me.

1176
01:13:11,310 --> 01:13:13,150
- Wu Yeol turned into a baby.
- Seriously.

1177
01:13:13,150 --> 01:13:15,900
- Just follow the pink line.
- Okay.

1178
01:13:15,900 --> 01:13:17,580
Watch out for the bump.

1179
01:13:17,580 --> 01:13:20,940
Gosh, I'm sorry.
I thought it was a fake bump.

1180
01:13:20,940 --> 01:13:22,210
I like stuff like this.

1181
01:13:22,210 --> 01:13:24,930
I like a woman who floors it
on the speed bump.

1182
01:13:24,930 --> 01:13:26,030
He likes everything.

1183
01:13:26,030 --> 01:13:29,720
- Nice. Nice, Wu Yeol.
- I don't do that.

1184
01:13:29,720 --> 01:13:31,270
It's because I've never driven here before.

1185
01:13:31,270 --> 01:13:33,620
- I think you should slow down.
- Okay.

1186
01:13:33,620 --> 01:13:36,710
He's a good driving coach.

1187
01:13:37,450 --> 01:13:40,170
What's this?

1188
01:13:40,170 --> 01:13:43,080
Is it telling me to take an exit?

1189
01:13:43,080 --> 01:13:46,190
You just need to take the first two lanes.

1190
01:13:46,190 --> 01:13:50,030
No need to stress.
Keep going straight and turn.

1191
01:13:50,030 --> 01:13:52,020
Keep going.

1192
01:13:52,020 --> 01:13:54,370
Keep going and turn now.

1193
01:13:54,370 --> 01:13:57,980
You're on the third lane. Let's turn here.

1194
01:13:57,980 --> 01:14:01,280
Go in now. That's right.

1195
01:14:01,280 --> 01:14:03,430
- Wu Yeol is so cool.
- I know.

1196
01:14:03,430 --> 01:14:05,180
Wow.

1197
01:14:06,280 --> 01:14:09,630
- You're a pro. Only pros hold this part.
- Really?

1198
01:14:09,630 --> 01:14:14,210
It's because somebody turned me into a pro.

1199
01:14:14,210 --> 01:14:18,150
- Not at all.
- It's hard to be that patient.

1200
01:14:18,150 --> 01:14:19,750
[Tap]

1201
01:14:19,750 --> 01:14:22,030
He's good. He's good.

1202
01:14:24,000 --> 01:14:26,380
What do you think? Is it thrilling?

1203
01:14:26,380 --> 01:14:28,080
You're good.

1204
01:14:30,360 --> 01:14:32,920
- I'm getting a headache.
- Really?

1205
01:14:32,920 --> 01:14:36,060
- The back of my head hurts.
- Really?

1206
01:14:36,060 --> 01:14:39,040
Should I massage your neck?

1207
01:14:39,040 --> 01:14:43,000
- What if I pass out?
- Her neck is so tiny.

1208
01:14:43,000 --> 01:14:48,460
What if I pass out from joy?

1209
01:14:48,460 --> 01:14:51,630
- I'm in heaven.
- I'm in heaven.

1210
01:14:51,630 --> 01:14:56,260
This is it, right? Is there more here?

1211
01:14:57,600 --> 01:14:59,600
Should I drive?

1212
01:15:00,860 --> 01:15:05,430
[Feeling much better]

1213
01:15:05,430 --> 01:15:07,670
- Let me know when you're tired.
- Okay.

1214
01:15:08,570 --> 01:15:10,930
Let me know when you're tired.

1215
01:15:11,950 --> 01:15:14,050
This is your first time, right?

1216
01:15:14,710 --> 01:15:18,200
- Be careful.
- Their banter is cute.

1217
01:15:20,640 --> 01:15:23,730
- I love your perfume.
- Really?

1218
01:15:26,300 --> 01:15:28,370
Maybe it's just your scent.

1219
01:15:28,370 --> 01:15:31,360
I'm wearing perfume today.

1220
01:15:34,040 --> 01:15:35,980
[This morning]

1221
01:15:39,200 --> 01:15:40,470
[Tap, tap]

1222
01:15:41,270 --> 01:15:45,070
[Finished getting ready with the perfume]

1223
01:15:46,670 --> 01:15:48,470
Do you still have it on your wrist?

1224
01:15:50,050 --> 01:15:52,400
Here's the rest stop.

1225
01:15:52,400 --> 01:15:53,800
Let's eat everything.

1226
01:15:53,800 --> 01:15:56,890
- Let's eat the entire rest stop.
- Let's eat the entire rest stop.

1227
01:15:58,650 --> 01:16:00,430
So cute.

1228
01:16:02,250 --> 01:16:04,690
Why does it look so good?

1229
01:16:05,500 --> 01:16:08,130
- It's crazy.
- They bought a whole bunch.

1230
01:16:08,130 --> 01:16:10,970
Get in first. Get in first.

1231
01:16:10,970 --> 01:16:12,440
Thank you.

1232
01:16:12,440 --> 01:16:15,360
[Bringing armful of food]

1233
01:16:15,360 --> 01:16:19,830
Those potatoes look amazing.

1234
01:16:22,660 --> 01:16:24,800
Let me know if you want the walnut waffle.

1235
01:16:24,800 --> 01:16:26,890
- I want it.
- She'll feed him.

1236
01:16:26,890 --> 01:16:28,910
Eat it.

1237
01:16:28,910 --> 01:16:32,090
He could have eaten it himself.

1238
01:16:32,090 --> 01:16:34,180
I'm starving.

1239
01:16:34,180 --> 01:16:36,490
Let's start eating.

1240
01:16:36,490 --> 01:16:41,550
[Wu Yeol is having a bite of a potato]

1241
01:16:41,550 --> 01:16:43,980
- Why is it so good?
- I know.

1242
01:16:43,980 --> 01:16:47,000
[The next is skewered sausage and rice cake]

1243
01:16:47,000 --> 01:16:48,440
[Big bite]

1244
01:16:48,440 --> 01:16:50,760
Hungry guy.

1245
01:16:51,690 --> 01:16:52,980
[Passing out]

1246
01:16:52,980 --> 01:16:54,070
She's so cute.

1247
01:16:54,070 --> 01:16:56,190
I'm glad I'm not eating and driving.

1248
01:16:56,190 --> 01:16:58,550
I would have passed out.

1249
01:16:58,550 --> 01:17:02,320
- Eat all you want, Yu Gyeong.
- Gosh, he's so sweet.

1250
01:17:02,320 --> 01:17:05,830
- Do you gain weight while in a relationship?
- I do.

1251
01:17:05,830 --> 01:17:08,590
I start gaining weight around here.

1252
01:17:08,590 --> 01:17:11,720
I don't look good. I can't gain weight.

1253
01:17:12,520 --> 01:17:13,780
[Two walnut waffles left]

1254
01:17:13,780 --> 01:17:15,650
They finished them.

1255
01:17:15,650 --> 01:17:18,000
Finish it. I'm full.

1256
01:17:18,000 --> 01:17:20,100
- Really?
- Yes.

1257
01:17:20,100 --> 01:17:21,980
I'll let you have one.

1258
01:17:21,980 --> 01:17:25,100
The last person to finish gains weight.
I'll eat it.

1259
01:17:25,100 --> 01:17:27,720
You'll gain weight here.

1260
01:17:30,440 --> 01:17:32,370
Don't run away from me.

1261
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:35,350
I want to run away.

1262
01:17:36,740 --> 01:17:39,520
- Let's try that sometime.
- He says "sometime."

1263
01:17:39,520 --> 01:17:42,310
- Taking a trip just to eat.
- A trip!

1264
01:17:42,310 --> 01:17:45,110
I love how he's talking about the future.

1265
01:17:45,110 --> 01:17:48,250
We'll drive around to try famous food.

1266
01:17:48,250 --> 01:17:52,780
Have you heard of the bread taxi in Daejeon?

1267
01:17:52,780 --> 01:17:56,900
What's famous here? Let's move on.

1268
01:17:59,220 --> 01:18:01,760
This is so nice. It's so romantic.

1269
01:18:01,760 --> 01:18:05,940
I have a question.
What's your usual dating style?

1270
01:18:06,630 --> 01:18:10,090
I love walking in the neighborhood
park with ice cream.

1271
01:18:10,090 --> 01:18:11,870
Me, too.

1272
01:18:11,870 --> 01:18:14,610
Going for a walk when the weather is nice.

1273
01:18:14,610 --> 01:18:18,370
- And eating tasty food there.
- Yes, take it to go.

1274
01:18:18,370 --> 01:18:21,680
- They are so happy together.
- I know.

1275
01:18:24,020 --> 01:18:29,700
Yesterday, we were a bit...

1276
01:18:29,700 --> 01:18:33,730
You didn't feel so great at first.

1277
01:18:33,730 --> 01:18:35,130
Will he talk about it?

1278
01:18:35,130 --> 01:18:37,650
You were doing the dishes alone.

1279
01:18:38,770 --> 01:18:41,790
- It was hard to approach you.
- Really?

1280
01:18:42,540 --> 01:18:46,370
I could tell you weren't in a great mood.

1281
01:18:49,660 --> 01:18:54,180
I think I was reading the room,
so I didn't know what to do.

1282
01:18:54,180 --> 01:18:55,460
He's feeling antsy.

1283
01:18:55,460 --> 01:18:58,210
[Wu Yeol kept circling Yu Gyeong]

1284
01:18:59,120 --> 01:19:03,150
As I felt lost, I didn't know what to say.

1285
01:19:03,150 --> 01:19:05,660
I felt like I couldn't control myself.

1286
01:19:05,660 --> 01:19:07,540
Is that right?

1287
01:19:07,540 --> 01:19:12,270
Like I was feeling tense around you?

1288
01:19:12,270 --> 01:19:15,720
- He's confessing his feelings.
- That's basically it.

1289
01:19:15,720 --> 01:19:17,300
Right.

1290
01:19:17,300 --> 01:19:19,740
- You mean, you become stupid?
- Yeah, I do.

1291
01:19:19,740 --> 01:19:22,890
Really? You feel nervous?

1292
01:19:22,890 --> 01:19:24,940
I do get nervous.

1293
01:19:26,590 --> 01:19:30,610
Whenever I'm with you, I forget everything.

1294
01:19:30,610 --> 01:19:33,440
- About what? The negative stuff?
- Yeah.

1295
01:19:33,440 --> 01:19:35,630
I just like everything again.

1296
01:19:37,760 --> 01:19:41,120
I really like to make you laugh.

1297
01:19:41,120 --> 01:19:43,820
I'm happy when you laugh, you know?

1298
01:19:43,820 --> 01:19:45,670
It's like the song.

1299
01:19:45,670 --> 01:19:49,110
"I love your smile."

1300
01:19:50,440 --> 01:19:52,360
Gosh...

1301
01:19:53,670 --> 01:19:55,110
Don't make that face.

1302
01:19:55,110 --> 01:19:57,150
She's so happy.

1303
01:19:57,150 --> 01:20:02,530
[Yu Gyeong's three facial expressions]

1304
01:20:05,110 --> 01:20:07,280
It's fun.

1305
01:20:07,280 --> 01:20:08,830
We're already here.

1306
01:20:08,830 --> 01:20:11,450
[What kind of stories will unfold
in their last destination?]

1307
01:20:11,450 --> 01:20:13,910
- There are quite a lot of people.
- I know.

1308
01:20:13,910 --> 01:20:16,800
- Is it popular?
- Of course.

1309
01:20:16,800 --> 01:20:18,130
It's a hot place.

1310
01:20:18,130 --> 01:20:21,200
- It's so cute.
- It's cozy.

1311
01:20:21,200 --> 01:20:24,700
- What beautiful weather.
- Even the weather is cooperating.

1312
01:20:24,700 --> 01:20:27,190
- Have you had Vin Chaud?
- No.

1313
01:20:27,190 --> 01:20:28,810
- You haven't?
- Isn't it this?

1314
01:20:28,810 --> 01:20:30,700
- Warm wine.
- Cold medicine.

1315
01:20:30,700 --> 01:20:34,020
- Cold medicine?
- It's for colds.

1316
01:20:34,020 --> 01:20:36,270
There's a car behind us.

1317
01:20:36,270 --> 01:20:38,170
So cute.

1318
01:20:38,170 --> 01:20:39,970
Thanks.

1319
01:20:41,030 --> 01:20:43,120
They look good together.

1320
01:20:43,120 --> 01:20:45,280
It's Chowon Photography Studio.

1321
01:20:45,280 --> 01:20:46,730
[The site for the movie
"Christmas in August"]

1322
01:20:46,730 --> 01:20:49,860
- From the movie?
- That's where it is.

1323
01:20:49,860 --> 01:20:52,440
"Christmas in August"?

1324
01:20:52,440 --> 01:20:54,480
Should we line up and take pictures?

1325
01:20:54,480 --> 01:20:57,190
Yes. Let's do that.

1326
01:20:57,190 --> 01:20:59,460
- How should we...
- Should we ask someone?

1327
01:20:59,460 --> 01:21:00,700
Do you want to go first?

1328
01:21:00,700 --> 01:21:02,570
- We'll take one for you.
- We'll do it for you.

1329
01:21:02,570 --> 01:21:04,460
- Thank you.
- Take it for them.

1330
01:21:04,460 --> 01:21:09,330
[Asking for a picture together
that will last]

1331
01:21:12,010 --> 01:21:14,960
- Please take lots.
- Thank you. What should we do?

1332
01:21:14,960 --> 01:21:16,660
Link arms.

1333
01:21:16,660 --> 01:21:19,690
- It's so awkward.
- Come on. Do a good job. Hurry.

1334
01:21:19,690 --> 01:21:23,040
- It's not like I can hold your hand.
- Go for it!

1335
01:21:23,040 --> 01:21:27,200
[Taking the first shot standing side by side]

1336
01:21:28,330 --> 01:21:31,280
My gosh. This is so nice.

1337
01:21:31,280 --> 01:21:34,020
That's a nice one, rather than
holding hands and stuff.

1338
01:21:34,020 --> 01:21:35,830
- It's much more exciting.
- I know!

1339
01:21:35,830 --> 01:21:38,020
My gosh. I love this one.

1340
01:21:38,980 --> 01:21:41,100
Thank you.

1341
01:21:41,100 --> 01:21:43,760
- Yes, we will.
- Yes, we'll take one for you.

1342
01:21:45,250 --> 01:21:47,590
One, two, three.

1343
01:21:47,590 --> 01:21:50,310
- Would you like to check?
- Thank you.

1344
01:21:50,310 --> 01:21:52,320
Thank you.

1345
01:21:52,320 --> 01:21:56,320
[Gunsan Railroad Town]

1346
01:21:56,320 --> 01:21:59,670
- Should we get some dalgona?
- Should we?

1347
01:21:59,670 --> 01:22:02,080
[To make dalgona]

1348
01:22:02,080 --> 01:22:03,940
It's coming together.

1349
01:22:05,620 --> 01:22:08,490
- It's done.
- I know. Should we just eat it?

1350
01:22:08,490 --> 01:22:10,160
Say ah.

1351
01:22:11,770 --> 01:22:13,450
Should we do an umbrella?

1352
01:22:13,450 --> 01:22:16,830
Let's do a heart.

1353
01:22:16,830 --> 01:22:20,730
Please press it down together. Press it hard.

1354
01:22:20,730 --> 01:22:25,820
[Heart dalgona that they made together]

1355
01:22:27,540 --> 01:22:30,770
It'd be weird if it breaks.

1356
01:22:32,350 --> 01:22:34,450
Take a picture of it.

1357
01:22:34,450 --> 01:22:40,010
[Another memory to remember forever]

1358
01:22:40,010 --> 01:22:43,760
- She's all happy now.
- I know.

1359
01:22:47,760 --> 01:22:50,070
- Scared me.
- Your reaction speed...

1360
01:22:50,890 --> 01:22:53,080
I've never done this before.

1361
01:22:55,230 --> 01:22:56,170
[Pop]

1362
01:23:01,310 --> 01:23:02,550
[Got a cat stuffed animal]

1363
01:23:02,550 --> 01:23:06,210
It's pretty cool when a guy
is good at those games.

1364
01:23:07,970 --> 01:23:10,620
- Do you like punching arcades?
- Punching arcades?

1365
01:23:10,620 --> 01:23:12,530
That's making me nervous.

1366
01:23:12,530 --> 01:23:14,030
Why?

1367
01:23:14,030 --> 01:23:15,910
I might break it.

1368
01:23:18,980 --> 01:23:20,560
At that rate...

1369
01:23:20,560 --> 01:23:22,590
She keeps feeding him.

1370
01:23:22,590 --> 01:23:25,630
- I didn't break it.
- You did a good job.

1371
01:23:25,630 --> 01:23:27,880
[Maintaining the heart]

1372
01:23:28,750 --> 01:23:30,570
[Crunch]

1373
01:23:31,760 --> 01:23:33,500
[Broken heart]

1374
01:23:33,500 --> 01:23:34,580
- What?
- What?

1375
01:23:34,580 --> 01:23:36,190
The heart broke.

1376
01:23:36,190 --> 01:23:37,740
What are you doing?

1377
01:23:38,810 --> 01:23:40,940
- This is wrong.
- Sorry.

1378
01:23:41,630 --> 01:23:43,470
Go get a new one.

1379
01:23:44,290 --> 01:23:47,030
- But that's not made by us.
- Cute.

1380
01:23:47,030 --> 01:23:48,670
Eat this here.

1381
01:23:50,760 --> 01:23:53,460
- Why?
- You're avoiding this.

1382
01:23:53,460 --> 01:23:56,970
- How did you do it?
- That's how sincere I am.

1383
01:23:56,970 --> 01:23:58,710
What is?

1384
01:23:58,710 --> 01:24:00,380
Heart?

1385
01:24:00,380 --> 01:24:02,010
[Heart]

1386
01:24:02,010 --> 01:24:05,140
You got a lot here. Both hands are full.

1387
01:24:05,140 --> 01:24:07,270
I got two stuffed animals.

1388
01:24:07,270 --> 01:24:09,660
It's a perfect date for Yu Gyeong.

1389
01:24:09,660 --> 01:24:12,220
You can see the train tracks.

1390
01:24:12,220 --> 01:24:14,510
One, two, three.

1391
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:19,880
- So pretty.
- She looks just like that stuffed animal.

1392
01:24:21,410 --> 01:24:22,950
Cute.

1393
01:24:22,950 --> 01:24:25,840
- Is there more of the train track?
- Daebak.

1394
01:24:25,840 --> 01:24:27,560
Let's go this way.

1395
01:24:28,480 --> 01:24:30,410
You want me to take a picture of you?

1396
01:24:30,410 --> 01:24:34,340
- The sun rays are so pretty.
- I believe you.

1397
01:24:34,340 --> 01:24:35,840
[Hunched over]

1398
01:24:40,890 --> 01:24:42,270
I want to take one.

1399
01:24:42,270 --> 01:24:44,610
Seriously...

1400
01:24:44,610 --> 01:24:46,430
He can just take any pictures.

1401
01:24:46,430 --> 01:24:49,090
It doesn't have to be good.

1402
01:24:49,090 --> 01:24:51,550
I'm greedy.

1403
01:24:51,550 --> 01:24:55,980
Yu Gyeong looks like a still cut
from a movie.

1404
01:24:55,980 --> 01:24:58,500
I see the ocean.

1405
01:24:59,660 --> 01:25:03,530
- Seagulls.
- The sound of the seagulls...

1406
01:25:04,510 --> 01:25:07,460
- Why?
- They're meowing.

1407
01:25:07,460 --> 01:25:09,040
Meow.

1408
01:25:10,280 --> 01:25:13,630
What should I do? Just walk?

1409
01:25:17,490 --> 01:25:20,210
- Stop.
- You're so handsome.

1410
01:25:20,210 --> 01:25:22,770
They just love it so much.

1411
01:25:22,770 --> 01:25:24,820
It's nice. It feels kind of...

1412
01:25:24,820 --> 01:25:26,360
- Peaceful?
- Yeah.

1413
01:25:26,360 --> 01:25:28,190
Gunsan is nice.

1414
01:25:29,110 --> 01:25:30,820
I'm hungry now.

1415
01:25:30,820 --> 01:25:32,750
I'm starving.

1416
01:25:34,480 --> 01:25:37,800
- So nice. What in the world...
- How long has this been?

1417
01:25:37,800 --> 01:25:41,210
Wu Yeol seems much different than before.

1418
01:25:41,210 --> 01:25:45,530
He might've given her butterflie
s in a more distant, mechanical way.

1419
01:25:45,530 --> 01:25:47,630
But now, he's a total puppy.

1420
01:25:47,630 --> 01:25:51,740
[Wu Yeol is acting all cutesy
with Yu Gyeong now]

1421
01:25:51,740 --> 01:25:53,000
That was so nice to see.

1422
01:25:53,000 --> 01:25:56,630
And they were talking
about their future trips.

1423
01:25:56,630 --> 01:25:57,700
They talked about their future.

1424
01:25:57,700 --> 01:26:00,530
Doesn't that sound like
"Let's pick each other tomorrow"?

1425
01:26:00,530 --> 01:26:03,070
- You can see it that way.
- That's what I wanted.

1426
01:26:03,070 --> 01:26:06,130
Didn't he mean indirectly,
"Come out tomorrow. I'll be there."?

1427
01:26:06,130 --> 01:26:09,800
That's right. And how they talked
about dating. It's for sure.

1428
01:26:09,800 --> 01:26:12,150
So, Wu Yeol kind of threw it out there.

1429
01:26:12,150 --> 01:26:13,760
- Totally.
- True. She'd think that.

1430
01:26:13,760 --> 01:26:15,160
Wu Yeol said both of those things.

1431
01:26:15,160 --> 01:26:16,840
Our Wu Yeol is different now.

1432
01:26:16,840 --> 01:26:19,600
He keeps tiptoeing around her

1433
01:26:19,600 --> 01:26:23,940
- and wants to adjust to make her happy.
- True, true.

1434
01:26:23,940 --> 01:26:27,090
[Under the warm winter sunshine]

1435
01:26:27,790 --> 01:26:33,220
[Waiting with a letter in hand]

1436
01:26:33,220 --> 01:26:35,500
Who is it? Oh, Jun Hyeon.

1437
01:26:35,500 --> 01:26:39,540
[The night before]

1438
01:26:40,530 --> 01:26:45,720
[Jun Hyeon received two letters]

1439
01:26:46,720 --> 01:26:51,430
[Who did Jun Hyeon choose?]

1440
01:26:51,430 --> 01:26:53,020
Who is it?

1441
01:26:57,150 --> 01:26:59,570
[Light steps]

1442
01:27:01,330 --> 01:27:03,670
[Hello]

1443
01:27:07,950 --> 01:27:10,890
[Jun Hyeon's last date is with...]

1444
01:27:10,890 --> 01:27:14,860
- It's so Yun.
- She's so cute.

1445
01:27:14,860 --> 01:27:16,520
Oppa!

1446
01:27:17,960 --> 01:27:19,490
[Hi]

1447
01:27:19,490 --> 01:27:21,630
She startled him.

1448
01:27:21,630 --> 01:27:23,170
You have a loud voice.

1449
01:27:23,170 --> 01:27:25,690
- You're so loud.
- Loud?

1450
01:27:25,690 --> 01:27:29,550
- It's a different side of her.
- So Yun's dates are fun.

1451
01:27:31,260 --> 01:27:34,660
I was interested in Jun Hyeon at first, too.

1452
01:27:39,950 --> 01:27:42,180
You're high maintenance.

1453
01:27:43,900 --> 01:27:46,640
You run up so cute.

1454
01:27:46,640 --> 01:27:48,520
- Hop, hop, hop.
- Surprise.

1455
01:27:48,520 --> 01:27:50,150
Jun Hyeon notices those things well.

1456
01:27:50,150 --> 01:27:52,630
My old nickname was baby rice ball.

1457
01:27:52,630 --> 01:27:54,410
It resembles you.

1458
01:27:54,410 --> 01:27:55,760
What?

1459
01:27:56,590 --> 01:27:59,890
The easiest one to talk to on a 1:1 date.

1460
01:27:59,890 --> 01:28:01,000
So Yun.

1461
01:28:01,000 --> 01:28:03,730
There were those moments, too.

1462
01:28:03,730 --> 01:28:06,240
They do have a connection.

1463
01:28:06,240 --> 01:28:08,730
- No way.
- What?

1464
01:28:09,930 --> 01:28:11,990
Is this you?

1465
01:28:11,990 --> 01:28:13,660
Being comfortable with each other
is important.

1466
01:28:13,660 --> 01:28:17,310
- The weather is crazy.
- It's crazy. It's spring.

1467
01:28:17,310 --> 01:28:19,800
Makes me wonder if Jun Hyeon
is interested in her, too.

1468
01:28:19,800 --> 01:28:21,880
Did you know who it was when you read this?

1469
01:28:21,880 --> 01:28:24,540
- Most definitely.
- Really?

1470
01:28:25,300 --> 01:28:27,330
- I knew it right away.
- But how?

1471
01:28:27,330 --> 01:28:30,890
Didn't we even talk about
something similar to that yesterday?

1472
01:28:30,890 --> 01:28:32,830
Did we?

1473
01:28:33,730 --> 01:28:35,610
[The night before]

1474
01:28:35,610 --> 01:28:38,560
I like those two together, too.

1475
01:28:38,560 --> 01:28:40,880
I'm terrible at grilling meat.

1476
01:28:40,880 --> 01:28:42,830
You're doing great.

1477
01:28:42,830 --> 01:28:46,340
I become so masculine in front of you...

1478
01:28:46,340 --> 01:28:48,290
[Cracking up]

1479
01:28:48,290 --> 01:28:52,530
- He said it himself.
- I'm usually so feminine in front of meat.

1480
01:28:52,530 --> 01:28:55,990
I remember this, too. For the first time,

1481
01:28:57,470 --> 01:28:59,440
you became Queen Jun Hyeon.

1482
01:28:59,440 --> 01:29:02,870
Jun Hyeon? We're having
a girls' talk. Want to join us?

1483
01:29:02,870 --> 01:29:05,370
[When So Yun was struggling]

1484
01:29:05,370 --> 01:29:07,450
It's okay.

1485
01:29:07,450 --> 01:29:09,590
Love always changes.

1486
01:29:09,590 --> 01:29:12,150
You don't know how hearts will change.

1487
01:29:12,150 --> 01:29:14,090
Jun Hyeon talked to them like that.

1488
01:29:14,090 --> 01:29:17,090
Let's talk like this often.

1489
01:29:17,090 --> 01:29:19,290
Queen Jun Hyeon.

1490
01:29:19,290 --> 01:29:21,660
Queen? I like it.

1491
01:29:21,660 --> 01:29:24,170
They banter nicely.

1492
01:29:24,940 --> 01:29:29,260
What happened back then?
You were stressing out about something.

1493
01:29:29,260 --> 01:29:31,930
Was it that day? When we had grilled tripe?

1494
01:29:31,930 --> 01:29:34,660
You sent me a text saying, "You can do it."

1495
01:29:34,660 --> 01:29:36,260
Wait a minute.

1496
01:29:36,260 --> 01:29:41,430
I think I was most touched
during my stay here.

1497
01:29:41,430 --> 01:29:43,590
Really? Why?

1498
01:29:45,010 --> 01:29:47,690
- What's wrong, So Yun?
- Huh?

1499
01:29:47,690 --> 01:29:50,160
What are you worried about?

1500
01:29:52,180 --> 01:29:57,050
While I was struggling
and feeling overwhelmed,

1501
01:29:57,050 --> 01:30:00,690
Jun Hyeon sent me a text.

1502
01:30:00,690 --> 01:30:04,110
It's good to watch YouTube.

1503
01:30:04,110 --> 01:30:06,200
You're good when you set your mind to it.

1504
01:30:06,200 --> 01:30:07,850
I can do it.

1505
01:30:07,850 --> 01:30:10,510
I see. It was an inside conversation.

1506
01:30:10,510 --> 01:30:13,470
He texted, "You can do it."

1507
01:30:13,470 --> 01:30:18,570
- The way he cared for me felt so...
- That's heart fluttering.

1508
01:30:18,570 --> 01:30:21,720
It strengthened me so much.

1509
01:30:22,470 --> 01:30:24,890
It made me wonder...

1510
01:30:27,091 --> 01:30:29,390
how you could comfort me
with such a short text.

1511
01:30:29,390 --> 01:30:32,510
- She remembered?
- He said it so nonchalantly.

1512
01:30:32,510 --> 01:30:37,170
A guy like that, who seems so cool
on the outside but is caring, exists.

1513
01:30:38,600 --> 01:30:41,240
And I also thought of this.

1514
01:30:41,240 --> 01:30:44,900
There were so many moments
where I didn't feel like myself.

1515
01:30:44,900 --> 01:30:47,340
Oh, really?

1516
01:30:47,340 --> 01:30:50,380
Each moment, I was being honest. But...

1517
01:30:50,380 --> 01:30:54,840
I had a change of heart, you know.

1518
01:30:54,840 --> 01:30:59,300
I did act awkwardly because of those things.

1519
01:30:59,300 --> 01:31:03,560
On the flip side, I think I'm so
myself when I'm with you.

1520
01:31:03,560 --> 01:31:05,520
In this house.

1521
01:31:05,520 --> 01:31:07,110
You're yourself?

1522
01:31:07,110 --> 01:31:09,380
I think this is real me.

1523
01:31:09,380 --> 01:31:11,130
I think so, too.

1524
01:31:12,660 --> 01:31:15,270
I think I was mostly myself with you.

1525
01:31:15,270 --> 01:31:18,780
- They're really opening up.
- Yes.

1526
01:31:21,080 --> 01:31:23,370
You just got this?

1527
01:31:23,370 --> 01:31:26,930
It'd be flattering if she finds
out he chose that.

1528
01:31:28,960 --> 01:31:30,390
He's not answering her.

1529
01:31:30,390 --> 01:31:32,880
Don't look down on Queen Jun Hyeon.

1530
01:31:32,880 --> 01:31:34,860
I'm kidding.

1531
01:31:38,000 --> 01:31:39,920
[Arriving in no time]

1532
01:31:39,920 --> 01:31:42,270
- We're here.
- Danyang!

1533
01:31:42,270 --> 01:31:45,120
- Thanks for driving.
- Thank you.

1534
01:31:47,350 --> 01:31:49,710
Wait, wait.

1535
01:31:49,710 --> 01:31:51,960
Gosh, what manner.

1536
01:31:51,960 --> 01:31:55,000
[I'll get the door]

1537
01:31:55,000 --> 01:31:58,380
- Why are you laughing?
- You're such a sweet guy.

1538
01:31:58,380 --> 01:31:59,880
He's so cool.

1539
01:31:59,880 --> 01:32:03,620
- I've never been here before.
- Me, neither.

1540
01:32:08,990 --> 01:32:10,760
Whoa, seriously...

1541
01:32:10,760 --> 01:32:13,170
- It's cool.
- So nice.

1542
01:32:14,400 --> 01:32:16,450
[Open view right in front of them]

1543
01:32:16,450 --> 01:32:18,870
But why is this frozen?

1544
01:32:18,870 --> 01:32:20,960
It's so warm, though.

1545
01:32:20,960 --> 01:32:23,050
But it's so pretty.

1546
01:32:23,820 --> 01:32:26,700
You know, we come to places like this often.

1547
01:32:26,700 --> 01:32:28,600
Yeah, famous sightseeing places.

1548
01:32:28,600 --> 01:32:31,800
[They also saw night city view in Japan]

1549
01:32:32,310 --> 01:32:36,690
[Must take pictures on a trip]

1550
01:32:38,050 --> 01:32:39,690
Polite hand.

1551
01:32:41,440 --> 01:32:43,640
- There are wings.
- He's so funny.

1552
01:32:43,640 --> 01:32:46,830
I found the wings I had lost.

1553
01:32:47,560 --> 01:32:48,780
- Did you take a good one?
- Totally.

1554
01:32:48,780 --> 01:32:50,390
- Do I look like an angel?
- Totally. An angel.

1555
01:32:50,390 --> 01:32:53,320
- But you look a little depraved.
- Depraved...

1556
01:32:53,320 --> 01:32:56,710
Jun Hyeon's sense of humor is so...

1557
01:32:56,710 --> 01:32:58,340
- You, too.
- No, no.

1558
01:32:58,340 --> 01:33:00,790
- Why not?
- Okay.

1559
01:33:00,790 --> 01:33:03,160
I'm doing this because you said so.

1560
01:33:04,470 --> 01:33:07,440
[I can pose for pictures, too]

1561
01:33:08,070 --> 01:33:11,870
Good, good. Paragliding?
It's good weather for it.

1562
01:33:11,870 --> 01:33:14,560
- Should we try it?
- We might as well.

1563
01:33:14,560 --> 01:33:16,230
- Really?
- Are they going to?

1564
01:33:16,230 --> 01:33:18,770
[Going for paragliding, specialty of Danyang]

1565
01:33:18,770 --> 01:33:20,760
Looks so fun.

1566
01:33:21,590 --> 01:33:23,650
[Cute helmet is a must]

1567
01:33:23,650 --> 01:33:25,680
He's so cute.

1568
01:33:26,620 --> 01:33:29,960
You will run toward that slope with me.

1569
01:33:29,960 --> 01:33:32,340
If you hesitate,
it could cause a big accident.

1570
01:33:32,340 --> 01:33:35,270
You're going... you're going with me, right?

1571
01:33:35,270 --> 01:33:37,850
The wind... It's windy. Is it okay?

1572
01:33:37,850 --> 01:33:42,240
Even though you're scared,
you have to keep running. Okay?

1573
01:33:42,240 --> 01:33:43,710
Okay.

1574
01:33:46,770 --> 01:33:51,550
[Jun Hyeon starts off strong]

1575
01:33:52,840 --> 01:33:55,470
Wow, how could he do that...

1576
01:33:55,470 --> 01:33:58,880
- Wow!
- So cool.

1577
01:33:58,880 --> 01:34:01,380
[A breathtaking, expansive view]

1578
01:34:01,380 --> 01:34:03,400
Oh, nice.

1579
01:34:04,590 --> 01:34:05,620
Fighting!

1580
01:34:05,620 --> 01:34:07,440
What's your name?

1581
01:34:07,440 --> 01:34:09,510
I'm Choi So Yun.

1582
01:34:10,540 --> 01:34:13,290
Okay, run, run, run, run!

1583
01:34:13,290 --> 01:34:15,180
[Nerve-racking first flight for So Yun]

1584
01:34:15,180 --> 01:34:20,890
[Scream]

1585
01:34:22,930 --> 01:34:25,520
Calm down. You're alive. Don't worry.

1586
01:34:25,520 --> 01:34:28,010
Gosh, I'm so, so scared.

1587
01:34:28,010 --> 01:34:32,250
Great! Look at the sunset.
Isn't it beautiful?

1588
01:34:32,250 --> 01:34:34,640
Whoa, it's like a painting!

1589
01:34:34,640 --> 01:34:36,230
This is crazy.

1590
01:34:36,230 --> 01:34:37,770
- Isn't it beautiful?
- Yes.

1591
01:34:37,770 --> 01:34:40,630
[So Yun is flying in the sky]

1592
01:34:40,630 --> 01:34:43,500
Say something to your loved one.

1593
01:34:45,350 --> 01:34:48,040
- My loved one?
- "My loved one"?

1594
01:34:48,040 --> 01:34:49,830
Open your arms.

1595
01:34:50,610 --> 01:34:56,390
[Surprisingly, having fun?]

1596
01:34:59,380 --> 01:35:03,190
Instructor, Happy New Year!

1597
01:35:04,050 --> 01:35:06,360
She's so cheerful.

1598
01:35:09,730 --> 01:35:12,140
Instructor. Instructor,
Instructor, Instructor!

1599
01:35:12,140 --> 01:35:15,600
Wait, our tailbone will break! Instructor!

1600
01:35:15,600 --> 01:35:17,200
Instructor!

1601
01:35:18,940 --> 01:35:21,480
[So Yun lands safely]

1602
01:35:23,470 --> 01:35:25,840
- That wasn't scary at all.
- Right?

1603
01:35:25,840 --> 01:35:29,290
- It's not a big deal.
- You didn't scream at all.

1604
01:35:30,260 --> 01:35:32,350
- That instructor is funny.
- Why did you scream so much?

1605
01:35:32,350 --> 01:35:34,080
- Did you hear?
- I heard everything up in the air.

1606
01:35:34,080 --> 01:35:35,420
He heard?

1607
01:35:35,420 --> 01:35:38,420
[Finishing with a photo]

1608
01:35:38,420 --> 01:35:39,700
How was it? Did you have fun?

1609
01:35:39,700 --> 01:35:42,640
Wow, it felt like a dream.

1610
01:35:42,640 --> 01:35:44,710
- Felt like a dream?
- Gosh, nice picture.

1611
01:35:44,710 --> 01:35:46,870
No one will outdo us today.

1612
01:35:46,870 --> 01:35:49,020
Nothing is better than this.

1613
01:35:49,020 --> 01:35:53,260
[Dinnertime before you know it]

1614
01:35:55,590 --> 01:35:57,670
[A Korean restaurant in Danyang]

1615
01:35:58,400 --> 01:36:01,550
Gosh, looks good.
Grilled garlic short rib patties.

1616
01:36:02,630 --> 01:36:03,960
[Nod]

1617
01:36:12,990 --> 01:36:15,010
Done?

1618
01:36:17,230 --> 01:36:19,040
He's so kind.

1619
01:36:20,400 --> 01:36:23,110
In the letter,

1620
01:36:24,670 --> 01:36:28,050
you talked about your true self.

1621
01:36:31,750 --> 01:36:35,470
Is your true self that much
different in your opinion?

1622
01:36:36,450 --> 01:36:39,870
- What you're afraid of...
- Good question.

1623
01:36:43,860 --> 01:36:46,220
I don't know how you see me.

1624
01:36:46,220 --> 01:36:50,400
In your view, am I very cheerful?

1625
01:36:51,760 --> 01:36:53,990
Not exactly, actually.

1626
01:36:53,990 --> 01:36:56,100
Really?

1627
01:36:56,100 --> 01:36:59,600
So, they like you for how cheerful you are,

1628
01:36:59,600 --> 01:37:01,620
but after getting to know you,
"She has this side, too?"

1629
01:37:01,620 --> 01:37:04,320
- You're right.
- Something like that?

1630
01:37:05,160 --> 01:37:08,020
I guess some people didn't like that, huh?

1631
01:37:11,980 --> 01:37:14,030
That could be understandable.

1632
01:37:14,030 --> 01:37:15,810
- I know.
- If they thought that?

1633
01:37:15,810 --> 01:37:17,160
I know.

1634
01:37:17,160 --> 01:37:20,630
Even if you behave the same way
with different people,

1635
01:37:20,630 --> 01:37:23,570
- that person can see it in a positive light.
- True.

1636
01:37:25,010 --> 01:37:26,630
So...

1637
01:37:28,110 --> 01:37:32,330
it means it's a deeper matter of the heart.

1638
01:37:32,330 --> 01:37:33,870
Right.

1639
01:37:34,910 --> 01:37:37,490
But if both people feel that way...

1640
01:37:37,490 --> 01:37:39,400
- It's tough.
- Tough.

1641
01:37:40,420 --> 01:37:43,150
True. It's not a shameful thing.
You have to meet someone compatible.

1642
01:37:43,150 --> 01:37:46,310
That's why I feel a little regretful.

1643
01:37:46,310 --> 01:37:49,910
You always say that. What are you
so regretful about?

1644
01:37:51,750 --> 01:37:57,290
I feel like I'm starting
to get to know everyone.

1645
01:37:57,290 --> 01:38:00,990
And they're telling us to choose tomorrow.

1646
01:38:00,990 --> 01:38:08,590
[Feeling regretful,
with only one day remaining]

1647
01:38:08,590 --> 01:38:12,690
I felt so flustered on the
first date I went with you.

1648
01:38:12,690 --> 01:38:15,690
Why? Did I do something wrong?

1649
01:38:18,080 --> 01:38:22,690
There was someone I really loved.

1650
01:38:23,930 --> 01:38:26,650
[The first date with Jun Hyeon]

1651
01:38:26,650 --> 01:38:28,530
- Not even a meal?
- No.

1652
01:38:29,600 --> 01:38:32,000
- Did you have breakfast?
- No, I didn't.

1653
01:38:32,000 --> 01:38:35,420
- They were both nervous.
- So different than now.

1654
01:38:35,420 --> 01:38:38,780
You were so similar to that man.

1655
01:38:39,610 --> 01:38:43,540
Your personality, MBTI, and how you date.

1656
01:38:43,540 --> 01:38:46,130
You were so similar to him.

1657
01:38:46,130 --> 01:38:50,240
You know how I went on three dates that day?

1658
01:38:50,240 --> 01:38:54,840
You left the most impression on me.

1659
01:38:55,990 --> 01:39:00,960
I wanted to get to know him the most.

1660
01:39:00,960 --> 01:39:07,170
Because I could see the similarity
with my ex.

1661
01:39:07,170 --> 01:39:10,120
That's when I wasn't so honest
with my feelings.

1662
01:39:11,010 --> 01:39:13,830
[She felt especially confused
after the date that day]

1663
01:39:13,830 --> 01:39:18,750
[So, she ended up texting Wu Yeol]

1664
01:39:19,410 --> 01:39:23,070
I think I pushed him away on purpose.

1665
01:39:23,070 --> 01:39:25,740
- My gosh...
- She's feeling so complicated.

1666
01:39:25,740 --> 01:39:28,650
Do you like something familiar
or something new?

1667
01:39:29,690 --> 01:39:34,310
My criterion has been
someone I fall for right away.

1668
01:39:34,310 --> 01:39:38,670
But I don't think that's it anymore.
That confused me a lot.

1669
01:39:40,820 --> 01:39:43,670
I don't want to disperse my energy.

1670
01:39:46,620 --> 01:39:50,240
[Feeling regretful about not being honest]

1671
01:39:50,240 --> 01:39:52,570
So Yun cried?

1672
01:39:56,740 --> 01:40:00,350
But after getting to know you,

1673
01:40:00,350 --> 01:40:04,410
you and he were totally different.

1674
01:40:04,410 --> 01:40:06,680
So Yun looks like a penguin.

1675
01:40:06,680 --> 01:40:08,220
A penguin?

1676
01:40:09,020 --> 01:40:10,710
I like penguins.

1677
01:40:10,710 --> 01:40:12,900
What's that?

1678
01:40:14,310 --> 01:40:18,520
The cute thing about penguins is
when they eat fish like this.

1679
01:40:18,520 --> 01:40:20,240
- Penguins are cute.
- You're cuter, Hyung.

1680
01:40:20,240 --> 01:40:22,280
- Are you drunk?
- No, I mean it.

1681
01:40:22,280 --> 01:40:24,460
No, no. He's not drunk.

1682
01:40:24,460 --> 01:40:26,940
I'm not drunk at all. I really like penguins.

1683
01:40:26,940 --> 01:40:28,970
Really. Even from outside of this house.

1684
01:40:28,970 --> 01:40:31,080
"From outside of this house."

1685
01:40:31,080 --> 01:40:32,960
Really.

1686
01:40:32,960 --> 01:40:35,620
You mean you don't like it in here, though.

1687
01:40:35,620 --> 01:40:38,780
But what's wrong with penguins?

1688
01:40:41,680 --> 01:40:44,320
Jun Hyeon, you were so scary.

1689
01:40:44,320 --> 01:40:46,020
- Scared?
- Everyone says that.

1690
01:40:46,020 --> 01:40:49,520
But it's not a negative fear.

1691
01:40:49,520 --> 01:40:56,160
It was a bit like how he puts me on my toes.

1692
01:40:56,160 --> 01:41:01,840
Whenever I said something,
I always felt conscious of you.

1693
01:41:01,840 --> 01:41:05,950
- Tiptoeing?
- Felt like he could read right through you.

1694
01:41:05,950 --> 01:41:10,230
So, whenever I said something,
I'd look over at him.

1695
01:41:10,230 --> 01:41:14,930
And he was staring at me like this.

1696
01:41:14,930 --> 01:41:18,060
What did you say you do when you argue?

1697
01:41:18,060 --> 01:41:20,230
I buy flowers and go to her.

1698
01:41:21,290 --> 01:41:26,240
Anyone can buy someone flowers
on an anniversary.

1699
01:41:26,240 --> 01:41:28,420
I only give them on an ordinary day.

1700
01:41:30,730 --> 01:41:37,090
I looked so happy in front of you.
I laughed a lot.

1701
01:41:41,140 --> 01:41:43,950
Actually, the two people I will choose

1702
01:41:46,860 --> 01:41:49,890
are very definite.

1703
01:41:49,890 --> 01:41:51,590
As for my choice.

1704
01:41:52,560 --> 01:41:58,350
So, I think the final choice can mark
the beginning of something new.

1705
01:41:58,350 --> 01:42:00,760
That's true. Yes.

1706
01:42:03,810 --> 01:42:07,020
So, tomorrow, I'll just...

1707
01:42:07,020 --> 01:42:12,100
pick the person my heart is drawn to.

1708
01:42:12,100 --> 01:42:14,460
No matter how much I thought about it,

1709
01:42:14,460 --> 01:42:19,040
I can decide not to pick him tomorrow.

1710
01:42:21,930 --> 01:42:23,560
I think so.

1711
01:42:25,350 --> 01:42:28,550
Your head hurts all of a sudden, huh?

1712
01:42:31,820 --> 01:42:36,170
[The weight of the final
choice is one step closer]

1713
01:42:38,340 --> 01:42:43,260
There are always regrets and
disappointments for the path not taken.

1714
01:42:43,260 --> 01:42:45,430
They're cute and look good together.

1715
01:42:45,430 --> 01:42:48,660
I don't think she's trying to win him over.
I think she was grateful.

1716
01:42:48,660 --> 01:42:52,400
I think his text to her made
such an impression on her.

1717
01:42:52,400 --> 01:42:56,620
And I think she wanted to
express her gratitude to him.

1718
01:42:56,620 --> 01:43:02,220
I think So Yun does see
Jun Hyeon as a man and a bit...

1719
01:43:02,220 --> 01:43:04,930
interested in him. It shows a little bit.

1720
01:43:04,930 --> 01:43:08,490
And all the ladies in the house

1721
01:43:08,490 --> 01:43:13,140
had said that they're attracted to Jun Hyeon.

1722
01:43:13,140 --> 01:43:15,400
He's like your brother,
yet an attractive man.

1723
01:43:15,400 --> 01:43:17,570
He's attractive in such a unique way.

1724
01:43:17,570 --> 01:43:19,820
Yes, totally.

1725
01:43:19,820 --> 01:43:22,260
[Gunsan date, on their way to a restaurant]

1726
01:43:22,260 --> 01:43:24,090
[The snack they bought at the market]

1727
01:43:24,770 --> 01:43:26,880
My goodness.

1728
01:43:26,880 --> 01:43:27,960
[Yum]

1729
01:43:27,960 --> 01:43:29,960
What's with you?

1730
01:43:29,960 --> 01:43:32,270
Can't I do that?

1731
01:43:32,270 --> 01:43:35,030
As if to feed Yellow.

1732
01:43:35,030 --> 01:43:37,600
So, why is it "My Dog, Yellow"?

1733
01:43:37,600 --> 01:43:40,440
- You know my nickname?
- How could he not?

1734
01:43:40,440 --> 01:43:42,670
It's over tomorrow.

1735
01:43:42,670 --> 01:43:44,850
Yu Gyeong, it's over tomorrow.

1736
01:43:46,330 --> 01:43:48,560
Actually, Yellow is...

1737
01:43:49,310 --> 01:43:54,100
what my fellow performers call me.

1738
01:43:54,100 --> 01:43:56,050
- She's like Yellow.
- Because she's gentle?

1739
01:43:56,050 --> 01:43:58,570
- Because I'm cute.
- You're right.

1740
01:44:00,090 --> 01:44:03,350
[Cute]

1741
01:44:03,350 --> 01:44:05,960
- My hands are so cold.
- Really?

1742
01:44:05,960 --> 01:44:07,900
- Really.
- Want me to hold them?

1743
01:44:07,900 --> 01:44:09,010
My gosh!

1744
01:44:09,010 --> 01:44:10,660
It's okay.

1745
01:44:11,500 --> 01:44:14,690
When I do this, you're like, "Ew..."

1746
01:44:17,500 --> 01:44:20,760
- Don't you want it?
- Do the "whoosh."

1747
01:44:20,760 --> 01:44:22,880
Whoosh!

1748
01:44:23,670 --> 01:44:25,130
And she does it for him.

1749
01:44:25,130 --> 01:44:28,460
[The two can't stop laughing]

1750
01:44:29,060 --> 01:44:30,350
[Staring]

1751
01:44:34,630 --> 01:44:36,060
[Pretty]

1752
01:44:37,070 --> 01:44:38,900
[Her broken reaction]

1753
01:44:44,280 --> 01:44:46,250
Yu Gyeong.

1754
01:44:46,250 --> 01:44:49,200
- But I think it's nice.
- Why?

1755
01:44:49,200 --> 01:44:51,200
The way I feel.

1756
01:44:51,870 --> 01:44:54,830
Really? What's it like?

1757
01:44:55,800 --> 01:44:58,290
My heart raced a bit.

1758
01:44:58,290 --> 01:45:00,540
It's important for your heart to be racing.

1759
01:45:06,280 --> 01:45:08,510
- Oh, my.
- What? Was he kissing?

1760
01:45:08,510 --> 01:45:10,660
That was pretty much it.

1761
01:45:16,430 --> 01:45:18,570
- What's she doing?
- Should we meet halfway?

1762
01:45:18,570 --> 01:45:22,560
- Oh, my. Look at this.
- Please, not that.

1763
01:45:22,560 --> 01:45:24,740
You weren't going to say that?

1764
01:45:24,740 --> 01:45:28,160
You weren't going to say that,
no matter what?

1765
01:45:31,050 --> 01:45:34,130
[A charcoal grill place in Gunsan]

1766
01:45:34,130 --> 01:45:37,560
[Bickering at the restaurant entrance]

1767
01:45:41,000 --> 01:45:43,840
- It's daebak.
- Do you like a place like this?

1768
01:45:43,840 --> 01:45:45,020
Looks so good.

1769
01:45:45,020 --> 01:45:47,820
- Look at the side dishes.
- Looks so good.

1770
01:45:50,650 --> 01:45:52,940
What do you want?

1771
01:45:52,940 --> 01:45:54,360
I like pork belly.

1772
01:45:54,360 --> 01:45:56,620
Let's have pork belly and shoulder.

1773
01:45:56,620 --> 01:45:58,030
Then, ribs and intestines.

1774
01:45:58,030 --> 01:46:00,250
- Let's eat it all.
- Eat it all? Great.

1775
01:46:00,250 --> 01:46:01,700
[Wu Yeol sets the utensils]

1776
01:46:04,250 --> 01:46:07,030
- Is it fresh kimchi?
- You like it?

1777
01:46:07,030 --> 01:46:08,860
[Putting it in front of Yu Gyeong]

1778
01:46:08,860 --> 01:46:10,560
You eat this.

1779
01:46:10,560 --> 01:46:12,870
The two sit close to each other naturally.

1780
01:46:12,870 --> 01:46:15,140
- Not facing each other.
- What do you like?

1781
01:46:15,140 --> 01:46:16,800
How big?

1782
01:46:16,800 --> 01:46:19,120
- It's good like that.
- Oh, yeah?

1783
01:46:19,830 --> 01:46:21,580
Looks so good.

1784
01:46:22,840 --> 01:46:25,790
[The meat is cooking]

1785
01:46:26,750 --> 01:46:31,000
- You want them small?
- Not too small.

1786
01:46:33,450 --> 01:46:35,430
- Do it well.
- They're so happy.

1787
01:46:35,430 --> 01:46:37,080
Sure.

1788
01:46:38,710 --> 01:46:40,260
Thanks.

1789
01:46:43,530 --> 01:46:45,530
How is it?

1790
01:46:45,530 --> 01:46:47,820
- Daebak.
- Really?

1791
01:46:51,500 --> 01:46:53,540
[Hehe]

1792
01:46:54,120 --> 01:46:55,710
Eat.

1793
01:46:55,710 --> 01:46:57,230
I will.

1794
01:46:57,230 --> 01:46:59,900
[Full of meat]

1795
01:46:59,900 --> 01:47:01,190
What's going on, you two?

1796
01:47:01,190 --> 01:47:02,330
[The meat fell]

1797
01:47:02,330 --> 01:47:04,690
I'll eat it. It's mine.

1798
01:47:04,690 --> 01:47:06,680
[Wu Yeol takes the meat that fell]

1799
01:47:07,430 --> 01:47:09,520
- Want some?
- You eat.

1800
01:47:10,390 --> 01:47:12,270
They're lovers.

1801
01:47:18,590 --> 01:47:22,990
[A shot of soju]

1802
01:47:24,390 --> 01:47:27,150
You struggled after drinking half a bottle.

1803
01:47:27,150 --> 01:47:28,310
I did?

1804
01:47:28,310 --> 01:47:31,400
Is it because we had half
a bottle and some cocktails?

1805
01:47:31,400 --> 01:47:32,640
[Swoosh]

1806
01:47:32,640 --> 01:47:34,570
Heart beating.

1807
01:47:34,570 --> 01:47:36,380
Right. That's what happened.

1808
01:47:37,530 --> 01:47:40,240
Then, drink just three shots today.

1809
01:47:40,240 --> 01:47:42,880
- I'll savor it.
- Savor it.

1810
01:47:42,880 --> 01:47:45,250
He says "Savor it"
to someone he really likes.

1811
01:47:45,250 --> 01:47:48,240
[Second grill pan already]

1812
01:47:50,710 --> 01:47:52,750
I think we eat meat often.

1813
01:47:52,750 --> 01:47:54,250
Us?

1814
01:47:54,250 --> 01:47:57,380
That's true. The seagulls...

1815
01:47:57,380 --> 01:48:01,810
Yeah. I keep thinking about it.

1816
01:48:04,860 --> 01:48:09,620
To think that this is
our last date on the show...

1817
01:48:09,620 --> 01:48:11,690
That's true.

1818
01:48:11,690 --> 01:48:13,370
I'm sad.

1819
01:48:13,370 --> 01:48:20,080
But I'm happy that I got to go out
with you on our last date.

1820
01:48:24,400 --> 01:48:25,596
Nice.

1821
01:48:25,596 --> 01:48:29,290
I would've been so sad
to not see you today.

1822
01:48:29,290 --> 01:48:31,870
- Really?
- Sad?

1823
01:48:31,870 --> 01:48:33,440
That's not it.

1824
01:48:33,440 --> 01:48:38,182
- I had to meet you today. No matter what.
- She's saying that?

1825
01:48:38,182 --> 01:48:40,844
Of course. Wu Yeol
is being so straightforward.

1826
01:48:40,844 --> 01:48:42,902
If you hadn't come out...

1827
01:48:44,015 --> 01:48:46,169
I think I would've just gone home.

1828
01:48:46,169 --> 01:48:48,190
They're both saying.

1829
01:48:48,190 --> 01:48:50,450
[Heart-shaped meat]

1830
01:48:50,450 --> 01:48:52,310
- They're battling who likes them more.
- It's just meat.

1831
01:48:52,310 --> 01:48:54,620
- So cute.
- It's not!

1832
01:48:55,530 --> 01:48:57,560
It's a heart.

1833
01:48:57,560 --> 01:48:58,740
[Take this heart]

1834
01:48:58,740 --> 01:49:02,470
They must've cut it in heart shapes.

1835
01:49:02,470 --> 01:49:03,930
[Cracking up]

1836
01:49:05,370 --> 01:49:10,010
- Is that the heart you broke earlier?
- Yeah. I'll give it back to you.

1837
01:49:10,010 --> 01:49:14,010
Since I got rid of it.

1838
01:49:14,010 --> 01:49:16,400
Anything else you want to eat?

1839
01:49:16,400 --> 01:49:19,080
- Anything else you want to eat later?
- He keeps saying "later."

1840
01:49:19,080 --> 01:49:21,950
- Let's go out to eat.
- Got it.

1841
01:49:23,160 --> 01:49:25,290
Later?

1842
01:49:25,290 --> 01:49:26,650
[Nodding]

1843
01:49:26,650 --> 01:49:28,900
He's nodding.

1844
01:49:28,900 --> 01:49:31,030
There is tons of stuff to do.

1845
01:49:34,200 --> 01:49:37,690
- Let's go and have a drink.
- Drink more?

1846
01:49:37,690 --> 01:49:42,400
- Today will never end.
- Totally enjoying the date...

1847
01:49:44,690 --> 01:49:47,630
It's a time-travel foodie place.

1848
01:49:47,630 --> 01:49:49,189
Should we travel through time?

1849
01:49:49,189 --> 01:49:51,835
They want to stay together
as long as they can.

1850
01:49:51,835 --> 01:49:56,175
[A Korean-style bar in Gunsan]

1851
01:49:58,170 --> 01:50:00,390
Raw skate.

1852
01:50:02,200 --> 01:50:04,700
[What kind of conversation will
take place in this late night?]

1853
01:50:05,330 --> 01:50:07,850
- Hello.
- Hello.

1854
01:50:07,850 --> 01:50:10,930
Please give us one boiled meat
and a bottle of soju.

1855
01:50:10,930 --> 01:50:14,920
- Gunsan is famous for skate.
- Skate?

1856
01:50:14,920 --> 01:50:17,890
But it's different from what you're used to.

1857
01:50:17,890 --> 01:50:19,900
But she can't have seafood.

1858
01:50:19,900 --> 01:50:22,260
You can't have them at all?

1859
01:50:22,260 --> 01:50:24,920
She can't really have it.

1860
01:50:24,920 --> 01:50:28,030
- Try it.
- Okay.

1861
01:50:28,030 --> 01:50:30,370
It's worth a try.

1862
01:50:30,370 --> 01:50:33,260
Okay. Then, give it to us like that.

1863
01:50:33,260 --> 01:50:35,270
We were convinced.

1864
01:50:35,270 --> 01:50:38,020
If you can't eat it, I'll eat it.

1865
01:50:38,020 --> 01:50:42,180
- Wow, thank you.
- Thank you.

1866
01:50:44,060 --> 01:50:48,130
[Gunsan-style raw skate]

1867
01:50:48,130 --> 01:50:51,040
- Want to try?
- Yeah. I'm curious.

1868
01:50:52,050 --> 01:50:53,920
Try it.

1869
01:50:53,920 --> 01:50:55,290
[Looking]

1870
01:50:57,800 --> 01:51:00,980
It doesn't smell fishy at all.

1871
01:51:00,980 --> 01:51:03,520
- It's not fishy at all.
- Right.

1872
01:51:05,090 --> 01:51:07,380
I'll try the skate with pork and kimchi.

1873
01:51:10,390 --> 01:51:11,780
She's going for that?

1874
01:51:11,780 --> 01:51:13,610
That's the power of love.

1875
01:51:13,610 --> 01:51:15,900
- Are you able to eat?
- Yes.

1876
01:51:15,900 --> 01:51:19,070
I'm a master. I can eat sliced raw skate.

1877
01:51:19,070 --> 01:51:21,190
Yellow, who eats raw skate.

1878
01:51:24,520 --> 01:51:26,100
You're doing great.

1879
01:51:31,560 --> 01:51:33,020
[Smile]

1880
01:51:34,150 --> 01:51:36,370
- Gosh, so pretty!
- What?

1881
01:51:36,370 --> 01:51:37,900
I love it.

1882
01:51:37,900 --> 01:51:42,020
"It's a total side dish for soju."
That's what I should say, right?

1883
01:51:42,020 --> 01:51:44,980
- You can say that.
- Right, right.

1884
01:51:44,980 --> 01:51:49,410
I'm kind of sad that today is the last day.

1885
01:51:49,410 --> 01:51:52,980
I said this to Min Ju.

1886
01:51:52,980 --> 01:51:57,050
"I don't really know much about Mr. Wu Yeol."

1887
01:51:57,050 --> 01:51:59,090
Mr. Wu Yeol?

1888
01:51:59,090 --> 01:52:03,120
I said I don't know. That I haven't
talked to you that much.

1889
01:52:03,120 --> 01:52:05,220
And she said, "You must know this."

1890
01:52:05,220 --> 01:52:09,210
I said, "I don't know." That's what happened.

1891
01:52:09,210 --> 01:52:13,220
I'm the least serious when I'm with you.

1892
01:52:13,220 --> 01:52:16,480
- You don't talk about anything serious.
- They didn't have serious talks.

1893
01:52:16,480 --> 01:52:20,200
- Go ahead and spill it.
- Spill it?

1894
01:52:20,200 --> 01:52:27,590
I've been living in Seoul since 2023.

1895
01:52:27,590 --> 01:52:30,400
I came to Seoul right after
I got discharged from the army.

1896
01:52:35,540 --> 01:52:39,140
You must know how to do things on
your own. You must be used to it now.

1897
01:52:39,140 --> 01:52:40,800
It's comfortable.

1898
01:52:40,800 --> 01:52:43,660
I feel uncomfortable
receiving help from others.

1899
01:52:46,780 --> 01:52:49,400
I'm comfortable doing things alone.

1900
01:52:49,400 --> 01:52:51,350
And since then...

1901
01:52:52,600 --> 01:52:56,420
But I think I've always done things alone.

1902
01:52:56,420 --> 01:53:01,320
I got used to doing things alone,
one thing at a time.

1903
01:53:02,760 --> 01:53:08,190
In the process, while I work or meet people,

1904
01:53:08,190 --> 01:53:12,510
I tend to act as if everything is okay.

1905
01:53:12,510 --> 01:53:14,780
I try to put up a front.

1906
01:53:15,590 --> 01:53:18,050
In actuality, it's not like that.

1907
01:53:19,270 --> 01:53:22,010
And I tried to cover it up.

1908
01:53:22,010 --> 01:53:24,390
That could happen.

1909
01:53:27,300 --> 01:53:30,200
You know, like pretending to be mature.

1910
01:53:30,200 --> 01:53:33,150
It's what the men said
about Wu Yeol in the beginning.

1911
01:53:33,150 --> 01:53:36,280
I think I pretended to be a
certain way in front of others.

1912
01:53:36,280 --> 01:53:38,350
He's opening up honestly.

1913
01:53:38,350 --> 01:53:40,750
He must've had some hard times.

1914
01:53:40,750 --> 01:53:42,700
[Hearing about Wu Yeol for the first time]

1915
01:53:42,700 --> 01:53:46,240
- We noticed that he tried to act mature.
- We did.

1916
01:53:46,240 --> 01:53:48,920
But I think I changed a lot after I got here.

1917
01:53:49,890 --> 01:53:53,110
Actually, when I see your facial expressions,

1918
01:53:53,110 --> 01:53:54,460
Yeah?

1919
01:53:55,160 --> 01:53:58,790
I thought you express your feelings well.

1920
01:54:02,160 --> 01:54:03,910
You were cute.

1921
01:54:06,540 --> 01:54:09,200
Yu Gyeong can't hold back.

1922
01:54:09,200 --> 01:54:12,010
- I'm having fun.
- Really?

1923
01:54:12,010 --> 01:54:13,330
What's with your facial expression...

1924
01:54:13,330 --> 01:54:16,350
I don't know why I'm making this face.

1925
01:54:17,160 --> 01:54:18,540
What is it?

1926
01:54:20,180 --> 01:54:22,990
[Cracking up]

1927
01:54:22,990 --> 01:54:26,780
I listen to music really loudly.
I get so excited and scream.

1928
01:54:26,780 --> 01:54:28,690
[Her honesty that made Wu Yeol smile]

1929
01:54:28,690 --> 01:54:30,590
When I saw that...

1930
01:54:30,590 --> 01:54:31,970
[Fussing around]

1931
01:54:34,300 --> 01:54:35,910
I liked it.

1932
01:54:40,540 --> 01:54:45,370
I'm not good at expressing myself like that.

1933
01:54:45,370 --> 01:54:48,170
And I'm not used to doing that.

1934
01:54:50,660 --> 01:54:53,260
So, I was a bit envious of that.

1935
01:54:53,260 --> 01:54:56,170
Accepting things as they are
and expressing them.

1936
01:54:56,170 --> 01:54:59,840
You don't have the right to tell me
not to think a certain way.

1937
01:54:59,840 --> 01:55:03,130
- That's why I'm not.
- You're so honest.

1938
01:55:04,310 --> 01:55:05,840
I was envious.

1939
01:55:07,100 --> 01:55:10,710
That's when I realized that
it's good to be honest.

1940
01:55:10,710 --> 01:55:12,810
It's a good thing.

1941
01:55:13,710 --> 01:55:15,280
Right.

1942
01:55:16,580 --> 01:55:19,600
I've realized so many things
ever since I came here.

1943
01:55:19,600 --> 01:55:22,870
I can't count. There are so many
things each and every day.

1944
01:55:22,870 --> 01:55:26,350
Wu Yeol is talking things out nicely.

1945
01:55:27,570 --> 01:55:31,800
Didn't you say you haven't dated
in about a year?

1946
01:55:31,800 --> 01:55:35,940
Not over a year. Almost a year.

1947
01:55:37,450 --> 01:55:39,460
Because you were too busy?

1948
01:55:39,460 --> 01:55:44,690
Since I'm in one place all the time.
Work, home, and cafe.

1949
01:55:44,690 --> 01:55:48,060
Don't people ask you for your
number when you walk around?

1950
01:55:48,060 --> 01:55:49,700
No, they don't.

1951
01:55:49,700 --> 01:55:53,620
It just worked out that way,
naturally, after some time.

1952
01:55:53,620 --> 01:55:58,220
True. If you don't go to new places...

1953
01:55:58,220 --> 01:56:00,820
I think there's that, too.

1954
01:56:00,820 --> 01:56:07,040
I try not to expect much
from the other person.

1955
01:56:07,040 --> 01:56:08,720
Really?

1956
01:56:09,750 --> 01:56:11,130
Why not?

1957
01:56:14,150 --> 01:56:15,920
I don't know. It's just that...

1958
01:56:18,830 --> 01:56:21,370
if I expect a lot,
I'd be greatly disappointed.

1959
01:56:21,370 --> 01:56:23,390
I think it's been like that.

1960
01:56:25,640 --> 01:56:30,090
- So, you step back.
- Yeah. I did do that.

1961
01:56:33,800 --> 01:56:36,070
What a coward.

1962
01:56:36,070 --> 01:56:39,260
I'm pretty much a coward.

1963
01:56:44,430 --> 01:56:48,440
But should I say someone worthy?

1964
01:56:48,440 --> 01:56:52,030
There wasn't anyone worthy of giving my best.

1965
01:56:52,030 --> 01:56:54,010
True. He wasn't into the person that much.

1966
01:56:54,010 --> 01:56:57,150
- Unexpected.
- Really?

1967
01:56:57,150 --> 01:56:59,240
"I think now is the time."

1968
01:57:03,760 --> 01:57:05,490
What's going on?

1969
01:57:07,670 --> 01:57:13,220
But I didn't feel what I feel now then.

1970
01:57:14,890 --> 01:57:17,250
So, I just lived like that.

1971
01:57:19,030 --> 01:57:22,520
But I'd try harder
not to go back to that now.

1972
01:57:22,520 --> 01:57:24,430
They're their first loves!

1973
01:57:25,160 --> 01:57:26,880
So exciting.

1974
01:57:34,580 --> 01:57:38,940
They can't look away from
each other. Oh, my gosh!

1975
01:57:41,460 --> 01:57:45,150
So, what you felt being here is...

1976
01:57:49,400 --> 01:57:52,760
One day, I realized that...

1977
01:57:55,110 --> 01:57:59,750
I had some feelings I was unaware of.

1978
01:58:03,670 --> 01:58:07,870
- And I struggled because of those feelings.
- This is for real.

1979
01:58:07,870 --> 01:58:10,850
And I saw part of myself
that I've not seen before.

1980
01:58:10,850 --> 01:58:13,880
And I don't know what that emotion is.

1981
01:58:13,880 --> 01:58:17,350
I got curious.
I wondered what you were thinking.

1982
01:58:18,310 --> 01:58:21,720
And what came of that...

1983
01:58:22,830 --> 01:58:27,210
I don't know how to say it. Jealousy?

1984
01:58:27,210 --> 01:58:29,800
It bothered me
when you went out with someone.

1985
01:58:29,800 --> 01:58:31,600
- Yu Gyeong is totally falling.
- She's fallen.

1986
01:58:31,600 --> 01:58:36,910
Wondering what you did.
What kind of date you went on.

1987
01:58:36,910 --> 01:58:39,600
- What did you eat?
- I love it when they talk about that stuff.

1988
01:58:39,600 --> 01:58:41,520
Me? Kalguksu.

1989
01:58:41,520 --> 01:58:46,480
- You can see the sunset in real time.
- Where did you go?

1990
01:58:46,480 --> 01:58:49,240
- You guys met early.
- I know.

1991
01:58:50,140 --> 01:58:53,980
- It feels awkward to me, too.
- He is jealous.

1992
01:58:53,980 --> 01:58:57,200
It's awkward, but I like it.

1993
01:59:01,570 --> 01:59:06,370
- So, I'll try harder to be honest.
- Gosh...

1994
01:59:12,060 --> 01:59:15,200
But I do feel it.

1995
01:59:15,200 --> 01:59:19,590
Not that you're awkward.
I can see that you're trying.

1996
01:59:24,300 --> 01:59:32,630
And if you weren't here,
would I have felt those things?

1997
01:59:33,840 --> 01:59:36,730
- Really?
- This is crazy.

1998
01:59:36,730 --> 01:59:38,850
I thought that, too.

1999
01:59:41,430 --> 01:59:44,830
- I didn't know.
- It's so moving.

2000
01:59:45,990 --> 01:59:48,800
- Thanks.
- He's thanking her.

2001
01:59:51,790 --> 01:59:54,290
They're going to get sick.

2002
01:59:57,480 --> 02:00:01,390
But I'm not all that grateful.

2003
02:00:03,640 --> 02:00:05,570
Thanks.

2004
02:00:05,570 --> 02:00:08,840
- "Thanks."
- I love that word, "Thanks."

2005
02:00:08,840 --> 02:00:12,040
- Going forward...
- "Going forward'?

2006
02:00:13,040 --> 02:00:15,730
I'll be the same.

2007
02:00:15,730 --> 02:00:17,070
Sounds good.

2008
02:00:18,070 --> 02:00:20,020
I want to change.

2009
02:00:20,910 --> 02:00:22,860
This is so nice.

2010
02:00:24,930 --> 02:00:29,430
- I'll ask about anything I don't know.
- My gosh. So moving.

2011
02:00:29,430 --> 02:00:31,140
You ask me, too.

2012
02:00:31,140 --> 02:00:32,820
Sounds good.

2013
02:00:32,820 --> 02:00:36,590
I think Wu Yeol met someone
he's never met before.

2014
02:00:36,590 --> 02:00:39,330
A perfect day 2.

2015
02:00:39,330 --> 02:00:40,740
This is so nice.

2016
02:00:41,710 --> 02:00:45,970
[Today was a perfect day in every way]

2017
02:00:46,730 --> 02:00:51,000
[Last return home to the Signal House]

2018
02:00:51,000 --> 02:00:53,630
I think your name is awkward.

2019
02:00:53,630 --> 02:00:55,720
"Wu Yeol oppa" sounds awkward to me.

2020
02:00:55,720 --> 02:00:57,950
- You don't have to call me by name.
- "Babe"?

2021
02:00:57,950 --> 02:01:00,690
I like to call people by their names.

2022
02:01:00,690 --> 02:01:03,020
Yu Gyeong.

2023
02:01:03,020 --> 02:01:05,450
Yu Gyeong.

2024
02:01:05,450 --> 02:01:07,160
I like it.

2025
02:01:14,370 --> 02:01:16,450
Copying Yu Gyeong.

2026
02:01:16,450 --> 02:01:18,220
[Making a face]

2027
02:01:20,300 --> 02:01:22,570
Something is missing.

2028
02:01:29,100 --> 02:01:31,060
- They're not holding hands, right?
- Is he holding her hand?

2029
02:01:31,060 --> 02:01:32,890
Where is your hand?

2030
02:01:33,820 --> 02:01:35,880
[Scratching]

2031
02:01:35,880 --> 02:01:38,540
[Scratching]

2032
02:01:38,540 --> 02:01:40,880
They're holding.

2033
02:01:40,880 --> 02:01:42,680
Mr. Driver, wait.

2034
02:01:44,400 --> 02:01:46,160
Oh, my gosh.

2035
02:01:50,290 --> 02:01:52,860
[Opening the window]

2036
02:01:52,860 --> 02:01:55,700
What's going on?

2037
02:01:55,700 --> 02:01:58,460
Sleepy? Sleep.

2038
02:01:58,460 --> 02:02:00,240
You think I can?

2039
02:02:00,240 --> 02:02:02,100
- She can't sleep.
- Really.

2040
02:02:02,100 --> 02:02:04,420
I don't think I can sleep.

2041
02:02:04,420 --> 02:02:06,210
Probably.

2042
02:02:08,930 --> 02:02:11,100
Mr. Driver, wait a minute.

2043
02:02:14,090 --> 02:02:15,860
Wait a minute.

2044
02:02:37,230 --> 02:02:39,200
[Looking]

2045
02:02:50,200 --> 02:02:53,060
[Chaos]

2046
02:02:53,060 --> 02:02:57,120
[Total chaos while watching those two]

2047
02:02:57,120 --> 02:02:59,920
It's so funny to see them
act like they're not.

2048
02:02:59,920 --> 02:03:03,100
[I can't watch this. It's so exciting.]

2049
02:03:03,100 --> 02:03:05,980
I feel like crying.

2050
02:03:09,400 --> 02:03:14,070
[Tightly holding hands]

2051
02:03:24,800 --> 02:03:26,370
What's wrong with your facial expression?

2052
02:03:26,370 --> 02:03:28,060
[Passed out]

2053
02:03:28,060 --> 02:03:29,710
Passed out.

2054
02:03:30,830 --> 02:03:32,840
I can't do this.

2055
02:03:34,900 --> 02:03:37,070
Why is your heart racing so fast?

2056
02:03:41,980 --> 02:03:45,090
- Why is your heart racing so fast?
- Me?

2057
02:03:45,090 --> 02:03:47,710
- I can feel it all.
- Really?

2058
02:03:53,020 --> 02:03:55,410
- I can feel it here.
- Really?

2059
02:03:55,410 --> 02:03:57,870
Since I have a pulse.

2060
02:03:59,220 --> 02:04:03,240
Come on. Why are you feeling my pulse?

2061
02:04:03,240 --> 02:04:05,830
[Checking her heartbeat]

2062
02:04:09,830 --> 02:04:11,990
It really is beating fast.

2063
02:04:15,000 --> 02:04:18,370
I didn't know it, either. I was like this

2064
02:04:18,370 --> 02:04:20,860
and felt something.

2065
02:04:20,860 --> 02:04:23,000
I can feel your pulse.

2066
02:04:23,000 --> 02:04:25,850
Why must you figure this out, too?

2067
02:04:25,850 --> 02:04:28,360
It's not that I figured it out.

2068
02:04:30,800 --> 02:04:33,300
Who are you?

2069
02:04:36,490 --> 02:04:38,840
- Let's take a selfie.
- Okay.

2070
02:04:38,840 --> 02:04:40,950
Let's take it like this.

2071
02:04:40,950 --> 02:04:43,860
- How, how?
- Like this.

2072
02:04:48,780 --> 02:04:51,150
I'll think about this a lot later.

2073
02:04:52,640 --> 02:04:54,070
Without me?

2074
02:04:54,070 --> 02:04:57,090
- It's too high.
- Okay. I'll step back.

2075
02:04:57,090 --> 02:05:00,120
- You have to do it like this.
- I look good.

2076
02:05:00,120 --> 02:05:01,900
[Grown to resemble each other
without even realizing it]

2077
02:05:01,900 --> 02:05:05,940
- Come on. Do a good job.
- It's not like I can hold your hand.

2078
02:05:07,460 --> 02:05:10,150
- Let's stop.
- Okay.

2079
02:05:10,150 --> 02:05:11,670
Well...

2080
02:05:13,450 --> 02:05:15,490
Just look friendly?

2081
02:05:18,990 --> 02:05:20,250
[Head tilt]

2082
02:05:21,590 --> 02:05:26,560
[As honest as we can]

2083
02:05:32,420 --> 02:05:34,110
I like you.

2084
02:05:37,150 --> 02:05:38,710
Me, too.

2085
02:05:46,380 --> 02:05:48,530
Stop it.

2086
02:05:48,530 --> 02:05:50,210
[Choking up]

2087
02:05:50,210 --> 02:05:53,860
Why am I tearing up? Why?

2088
02:05:53,860 --> 02:05:56,250
[It's so touching]

2089
02:05:56,250 --> 02:05:57,920
Gosh, it's the ultimate.

2090
02:05:57,920 --> 02:06:00,210
I was touched...

2091
02:06:00,210 --> 02:06:02,880
I dated my wife for a short time
before we got married.

2092
02:06:02,880 --> 02:06:07,620
Someone like Yu Gyeong changes a person.

2093
02:06:07,620 --> 02:06:11,950
That's what really touched me.

2094
02:06:11,950 --> 02:06:14,920
Wu Yeol has changed.
Why? Because of Yu Gyeong.

2095
02:06:14,920 --> 02:06:17,620
Falling in love with someone
while tiptoeing around her

2096
02:06:17,620 --> 02:06:21,640
is an experience,
and he will love her greatly.

2097
02:06:21,640 --> 02:06:26,870
There were difficulties that
we've all witnessed. But...

2098
02:06:26,870 --> 02:06:29,360
[Tearing up again]

2099
02:06:29,360 --> 02:06:32,670
All they did was hold a hand
after having such a difficult time.

2100
02:06:32,670 --> 02:06:36,370
But it really brings us to tears.

2101
02:06:36,370 --> 02:06:38,160
That's what Hear Signal is all about.

2102
02:06:38,160 --> 02:06:40,520
But we've never had it this hard.

2103
02:06:40,520 --> 02:06:43,400
Right. It's your first time
crying on the show, right?

2104
02:06:43,400 --> 02:06:47,040
- You know, I'm never like this.
- You were touched before.

2105
02:06:47,040 --> 02:06:50,550
I feel like all the heartbreak I've had...

2106
02:06:50,550 --> 02:06:53,770
It's a happily-ever-after ending.
I don't want to know what happens after.

2107
02:06:53,770 --> 02:06:55,300
Totally.

2108
02:06:55,300 --> 02:06:59,300
But Yu Gyeong has been waiting
for a confirmation like this.

2109
02:06:59,300 --> 02:07:03,100
She was afraid because she
didn't feel this confirmation.

2110
02:07:03,100 --> 02:07:06,200
That fear disappeared
with the two holding hands

2111
02:07:06,200 --> 02:07:09,640
and through Tsuki and Eana's tears.

2112
02:07:09,640 --> 02:07:11,680
Because of their secret hand-holding.

2113
02:07:11,680 --> 02:07:15,020
But I felt more because of this
rather than holding hands.

2114
02:07:15,020 --> 02:07:20,000
Yu Gyeong never played any games.
Enough to be frustrating.

2115
02:07:20,000 --> 02:07:22,230
She was pure and always honest.

2116
02:07:22,230 --> 02:07:26,780
When we watched, we felt like
she was falling for him too easily.

2117
02:07:26,780 --> 02:07:30,920
But I see that it ultimately worked.
That's why I'm so touched.

2118
02:07:30,920 --> 02:07:33,860
It worked out in the end...

2119
02:07:33,860 --> 02:07:40,040
and holding hands at the end
made it complete.

2120
02:07:40,040 --> 02:07:42,660
[Keeps crying]

2121
02:07:42,660 --> 02:07:46,310
Gosh, she's at it again.
What's wrong with you?

2122
02:07:46,310 --> 02:07:49,620
I can't do this. I can't think too deeply.

2123
02:07:49,620 --> 02:07:51,360
It's so funny.

2124
02:07:51,360 --> 02:07:54,380
- It's the last sunset.
- This is so moving.

2125
02:07:56,120 --> 02:07:58,890
We never imagined we'd feel this way.

2126
02:07:58,890 --> 02:08:02,610
I saw the bed,
but I can't sleep on it anymore.

2127
02:08:02,610 --> 02:08:03,920
Stop.

2128
02:08:05,070 --> 02:08:10,460
Oppa, you gave me the greatest
happiness and the greatest pain.

2129
02:08:10,460 --> 02:08:14,220
I wanted to ask if you thought
of me as just a friend.

2130
02:08:14,220 --> 02:08:16,380
You were always there.

2131
02:08:19,350 --> 02:08:22,480
I recognized your letter right away.

2132
02:08:22,480 --> 02:08:25,030
Because I like you.

2133
02:08:26,440 --> 02:08:29,470
This is the last conversation
we can have here.

2134
02:08:29,470 --> 02:08:30,910
I won't regret it anymore.

2135
02:08:30,910 --> 02:08:33,670
I have the courage
to like someone with my best.

2136
02:08:33,670 --> 02:08:35,540
I want to say something.

2137
02:08:35,540 --> 02:08:38,460
I hope I get a chance to say that to you.

2138
02:08:39,650 --> 02:08:43,340
In the past month,
I think you were my everything.

2139
02:08:43,340 --> 02:08:46,440
Because there were feelings
that we had exchanged.

2140
02:08:46,440 --> 02:08:47,900
It's me.

2141
02:08:47,900 --> 02:08:50,520
You were the coolest in my eyes.

2142
02:08:50,520 --> 02:08:52,560
I've really thought about it a lot.

2143
02:08:52,560 --> 02:08:54,210
Hello?

2144
02:08:54,210 --> 02:08:57,010
And I tried to deny it.

2145
02:08:57,010 --> 02:08:59,620
My final choice is...

2146
02:08:59,620 --> 02:09:01,100
It's you.

2147
02:09:03,310 --> 02:09:05,150
Hurry over.

2148
02:09:06,744 --> 02:09:09,130
I always wanted to give it my all.

2149
02:09:09,130 --> 02:09:11,645
I hope my heart for you
is an encouragement for you.

2150
02:09:11,645 --> 02:09:15,855
In any case, I think it's you, Oppa.

2151
02:09:16,660 --> 02:09:18,320
I like you.
